t%3D%5C%22Soviet%20Submarine%20And%20US%20Aircraft%20Carrier%20Collide%5C%22%20charset%3D%5C%22%5C%22%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fi.insider.com%2F65f89c6e4af076d3cf91733d%3Fformat%3Djpeg%5C%22%20height%3D%5C%22396%5C%22%3E%3Cfigcaption%3EIn%20this%20aerial%20image%2C%20a%20Soviet%20Union%20submarine%20is%20seen%20after%20colliding%20with%20U.S.%20Kitty%20Hawk%20on%20March%2022%2C%201984%20in%20at%20sea.%3Cp%3EThe%20Asahi%20Shimbun%2FGetty%20Images%3C%2Fp%3E%3C%2Ffigcaption%3E%3C%2Ffigure%3E%3Cul%3E%3Cli%3EForty%20years%20ago%20today%2C%20a%20Soviet%20submarine%20collided%20with%20the%20US%20Navy%20aircraft%20carrier%20USS%20Kitty%20Hawk.%3C%2Fli%3E%3Cli%3EThe%20collision%20occurred%20as%20the%20sub%20was%20spying%20on%20US%20warships%20amid%20Cold%20War%20tensions.%3C%2Fli%3E%3Cli%3EIt%20was%20the%20third%20instance%20of%20a%20Soviet%20vessel%20colliding%20with%20an%20American%20one%20in%20just%20five%20months.%3C%2Fli%3E%3C%2Ful%3E%3Cp%3ELate%20at%20night%20on%20March%2021%2C%201984%2C%20sailors%20aboard%20the%20US%20Navy%20aircraft%20carrier%20USS%20Kitty%20Hawk%20felt%20a%20sudden%20jolt%20while%20sailing%20in%20the%20Sea%20of%20Japan.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThose%20aboard%20the%20carrier%20didn't%20know%20it%20yet%2C%20but%20their%2080%2C000-ton%20ship%20had%20just%20collided%20with%20a%205%2C200-ton%20Soviet%20attack%20submarine.%20The%20surprise%20collision%20came%20amid%20heightened%20Cold%20War%20tensions%20between%20the%20US%20and%20Soviet%20Union.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BI%20was%20on%20the%20bridge%20at%20the%20time%20of%20the%20incident%2C%20monitoring%20one%20of%20the%20two%20radars%2C%26quot%3B%20Capt.%20David%20N.%20Rogers%2C%20the%20carrier's%20skipper%2C%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.upi.com%2FArchives%2F1984%2F03%2F22%2FThe-skipper-of-the-USS-Kitty-Hawk-said-Thursday%2F7600448779600%2F%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Etold%20%3C%2Fa%3Ereporters%20shortly%20after%20the%20odd%20incident.%20%26quot%3BWe%20felt%20a%20sudden%20shudder%2C%20a%20fairly%20violent%20shudder.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3ENavy%20helicopters%20were%20quickly%20sortied%20to%20check%20out%20the%20situation.%20The%20New%20York%20Times%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.nytimes.com%2F1984%2F03%2F22%2Fworld%2Fsoviet-sub-and-us-ship-collide.html%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Ereported%3C%2Fa%3E%20at%20the%20time%20that%20the%20collision%20%E2%80%94%20which%20occurred%2040%20years%20ago%20Thursday%E2%80%94%20left%20the%20Kitty%20Hawk%20with%20a%20only%20a%20minor%20superficial%20dent%20while%20the%20Soviet%20submarine%20K-314%20appeared%20to%20have%20more%20serious%20problems.%20The%20vessel%20was%20unresponsive%20and%20unable%20to%20get%20moving%20under%20its%20own%20power.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EA%20Soviet%20missile%20cruiser%20accompanying%20the%20submarine%20dismissed%20American%20offers%20of%20assistance%2C%20according%20to%20US%20officials.%3Cstrong%3E%3Cem%3E%20%3C%2Fem%3E%3C%2Fstrong%3EThe%20aircraft%20carrier%20immediately%20resumed%20operations%20following%20the%20tense%20collision.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20Kitty%20Hawk%2C%20part%20of%20Battle%20Group%20Bravo%2C%20was%20sailing%20in%20the%20Sea%20of%20Japan%20for%20exercise%20Team%20Spirit%2084-1%20when%20the%20accidental%20collision%20occurred.%20This%20was%20just%20one%20of%20the%20military%20exercises%20in%20the%20series%20called%20Team%20Spirit%20that%20the%20US%20had%20participated%20in%20with%20South%20Korea%20over%20the%20course%20of%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.globalsecurity.org%2Fmilitary%2Fops%2Fteam-spirit.htm%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3E19%20years%3C%2Fa%3E.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cfigure%3E%3Cimg%20width%3D%5C%22594%5C%22%20alt%3D%5C%22A%20Korean%20Navy%20tank%20landing%20ship%20approaches%20the%20beach%20during%20exercise%20Team%20Spirit%20'82.%5C%22%20charset%3D%5C%22%5C%22%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fi.insider.com%2F65f8a0444af076d3cf917577%3Fformat%3Djpeg%5C%22%20height%3D%5C%22395%5C%22%3E%3Cfigcaption%3EA%20Korean%20Navy%20tank%20landing%20ship%20approaches%20the%20beach%20during%20exercise%20Team%20Spirit%20'82.%3Cp%3EHUM%20Images%2FUniversal%20Images%20Group%2FGetty%20Images%3C%2Fp%3E%3C%2Ffigcaption%3E%3C%2Ffigure%3E%3Cp%3EDuring%20the%20Cold%20War%2C%20Soviet%20subs%20would%20often%20follow%20US%20vessels%20closely%20to%20gather%20intelligence%2C%20and%20USSR%20submarine%20K-314%20had%20been%20following%20the%20carrier%20for%20several%20days%20prior%20to%20the%20collision.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EUS%20military%20officials%20were%20puzzled%20as%20to%20how%20the%20Victor%20I-class%20submarine%20didn't%20see%20the%20carrier%20before%20running%20into%20it.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BQuite%20honestly%2C%20I%20have%20to%20question%20the%20seamanship%20of%20the%20Soviet%20captain%20involved%2C%26quot%3B%20a%20Navy%20officer%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.washingtonpost.com%2Farchive%2Fpolitics%2F1984%2F03%2F22%2Fsoviet-sub-bumps-into-us-carrier%2F3c75515e-d492-4f6a-8f01-a023b6bc4c9c%2F%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Etold%3C%2Fa%3E%20The%20Washington%20Post%20after%20the%20collision.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EWhen%20the%20maritime%20accident%20occurred%2C%20submarine%20K-314%2C%20which%20typically%20held%20around%2090%20crew%20members%2C%20was%20following%20a%20Soviet%20guided-missile%20cruiser%20headed%20north.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BThe%20first%20thought%20was%20that%20the%20conning%20tower%20had%20been%20destroyed%20and%20the%20submarine's%20body%20was%20cut%20to%20pieces%2C%26quot%3B%20%3Ca%20rel%3D%5C%22noreferrer%5C%22%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.e-reading.club%2Fchapter.php%2F1010019%2F54%2FCherkashin_-_Vozmutiteli_glubin._Sekretnye_operacii_sovetskih_podvodnyh_lodok_v_gody_holodnoy_voyny.html%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Erecalled%3C%2Fa%3E%20Capt.%20Vladimir%20Evseenko%2C%20the%20submarine's%20commander%2C%20in%20an%20excerpt%20from%20Nikolay%20Cherkashin's%202011%20book%2C%20%26quot%3BDisturbers%20of%20the%20Depths.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cfigure%3E%3Cimg%20width%3D%5C%22594%5C%22%20alt%3D%5C%22Soviet%20Submarine%20And%20US%20Aircraft%20Carrier%20Collide%5C%22%20charset%3D%5C%22%5C%22%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fi.insider.com%2F65f89ceb4af076d3cf917369%3Fformat%3Djpeg%5C%22%20height%3D%5C%22396%5C%22%3E%3Cfigcaption%3EThe%20Soviet%20K-314%20after%20colliding%20with%20the%20Kitty%20Hawk%20in%201984%20on%20the%20Sea%20of%20Japan.%3Cp%3EThe%20Asahi%20Shimbun%2FGetty%20Images%3C%2Fp%3E%3C%2Ffigcaption%3E%3C%2Ffigure%3E%3Cp%3EEvseenko%20initially%20thought%20that%20the%20American%20carrier%20that%20had%20%26quot%3Brammed%26quot%3B%20his%20submarine%20that%20night%2C%20saying%20that%20the%20carrier%20hit%20the%20propeller%20and%20bent%20the%20stabilizer.%20Afterwards%2C%20the%20commander%20and%20his%20team%20found%20that%20the%20collision%20was%20the%20result%20of%20certain%20miscalculations%20on%20their%20end.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EEvseenko%20was%20then%20removed%20from%20his%20post%20after%20the%20incident%20and%20transferred%20to%20land%20operations.%20%26quot%3BFor%20me%20this%20was%20a%20blow%20worse%20than%20a%20blow%20to%20the%20propellers%2C%26quot%3B%20he%20said%2C%20according%20to%20a%20translation.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThis%20was%20third%20instance%20of%20a%20Soviet%20warship%20colliding%20with%20a%20US%20military%20vessel%20in%20a%20period%20of%20just%20five%20months.%20Prior%20to%20this%20collision%2C%20in%20October%201983%2C%20a%20Soviet%20submarine%20had%20to%20be%20towed%20to%20Cuba%20after%20it%20interfered%20with%20a%20US%20frigate's%20sonar%20device%20and%20was%20disabled%20%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EIn%201972%2C%20the%20Soviets%20signed%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2F2009-2017.state.gov%2Ft%2Fisn%2F4791.htm%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Ean%20accord%3C%2Fa%3E%20with%20the%20US%20in%20which%20the%20two%20pledged%20not%20to%20interfere%20with%20each%20other's%20naval%20operations%2C%20in%20part%20to%20help%20reduce%20the%20number%20of%20collisions%20at%20sea%2C%20a%20problem%20during%20the%20Cold%20War%20as%20US%20and%20Russian%20vessels%20often%20found%20themselves%20in%20close%20proximity.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EEven%20after%20this%20agreement%20was%20signed%2C%20accidents%20continued%20to%20happen.%20A%20major%20collision%20occurred%20in%20November%201974%20when%20American%20and%20Soviet%20nuclear%20submarines%20ran%20into%20one%20another%20near%20Scotland%2C%20coming%20extremely%20close%20to%20sinking%20one%20another.%20That%20incident%3Cstrong%3E%20%3C%2Fstrong%3Ewas%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.theguardian.com%2Fus-news%2F2017%2Fjan%2F25%2Fnuclear-submarine-collision-cold-war-cia-scotland%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Erevealed%3C%2Fa%3E%20in%20a%20CIA%20memo%20declassified%20in%202017.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EAnd%20such%20incidents%20at%20sea%20still%20happen%20even%20now%2C%20decades%20later.%20The%20last%20time%20American%20military%20vessels%20collided%20with%20a%20foreign%20ship%20or%20submarine%20was%20in%202017%2C%20when%20US%20Navy%20destroyers%20USS%20Fitzgerald%20and%20USS%20John%20S.%20McCain%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fuss-fitzgerald-sailors-punished-7-2017-8%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Ecollided%3C%2Fa%3E%20with%20the%20tanker%20Alnic%20MC%20and%20container%20ship%20ACX%20Crystal.%20respectively.%20The%20incidents%20were%20fatal.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cfigure%3E%3Cimg%20width%3D%5C%22594%5C%22%20alt%3D%5C%22USS%20Kitty%20Hawk%5C%22%20charset%3D%5C%22%5C%22%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fi.insider.com%2F65f9c236895d8220303243ab%3Fformat%3Djpeg%5C%22%20height%3D%5C%22446%5C%22%3E%3Cfigcaption%3EThe%20former%20aircraft%20carrier%20Kitty%20Hawk%20sits%20off%20the%20coast%20of%20Long%20Beach%2C%20CA%2C%20on%20the%20way%20from%20Bremerton%2C%20WA%2C%20to%20a%20Texas%20ship-breaking%20company%20on%20Monday%2C%20January%2024%2C%202022.%3Cp%3EJeff%20Gritchen%2FOrange%20County%20Register%2FSCNG%3C%2Fp%3E%3C%2Ffigcaption%3E%3C%2Ffigure%3E%3Cp%3EIt's%20unclear%20what%20ultimately%20happened%20to%20submarine%20K-314%2C%20but%20the%20Kitty%20Hawk%20continued%20to%20serve%20t