he%20Ministry%20of%20Environment%2C%20Forests%20and%20Climate%20Change%20(MOEFCC)%20released%20a%C2%A0%3Ca%20rel%3D%5C%22noopener%20external%20noreferrer%5C%22%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fimgs.mongabay.com%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2Fsites%2F30%2F2024%2F03%2F19121803%2FFeb-2024-tree-planting-methodology-GCP.pdf%5C%22%20data-wpel-link%3D%5C%22external%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Edetailed%20methodology%3C%2Fa%3E%C2%A0for%20a%20component%20of%20its%C2%A0%3Ca%20rel%3D%5C%22noopener%20noreferrer%5C%22%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Findia.mongabay.com%2F2023%2F07%2Fgreen-credit-scheme-encourages-environment-friendly-behaviour-but-needs-strong-regulation-to-work%2F%5C%22%20data-wpel-link%3D%5C%22internal%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3EGreen%20Credit%20Programme%3C%2Fa%3E%2C%20effectively%20enabling%20the%20trade%20of%20environmental%20benefits%20arising%20from%20tree%20planting.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20Union%20government%20calls%20the%20programme%20an%20%E2%80%9Cinnovative%20market-based%20mechanism%20designed%20to%20incentivise%20voluntary%20environmental%20actions%20across%20diverse%20sectors.%E2%80%9D%20But%20environmentalists%20and%20policy%20experts%20are%20wary%20about%20the%20extent%20to%20which%20market%20forces%20can%20support%20conservation%20and%20sustainability%20goals.%20The%C2%A0%3Ca%20rel%3D%5C%22noopener%20external%20noreferrer%5C%22%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fegazette.gov.in%2FWriteReadData%2F2023%2F249377.pdf%5C%22%20data-wpel-link%3D%5C%22external%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Efine%20print%3C%2Fa%3E%C2%A0of%20the%20scheme%20says%20the%20objective%20is%20to%20%E2%80%9Cencourage%20industries%2C%20companies%20and%20other%20entities%20to%20meet%20their%20existing%20obligations%2C%E2%80%9D%20under%20current%20compliance%20laws%2C%20while%20also%20encouraging%20%E2%80%9Cother%20persons%20and%20entities%E2%80%9D%20to%20participate%20voluntarily.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20methodology%2C%20issued%20in%20February%2C%20encourages%20large-scale%20tree%20planting%20on%20open%20forests%20and%20scrub%20lands%2C%20among%20other%20land%20types%2C%20to%20generate%20credits.%20These%20credits%20can%20be%20bought%20to%20meet%20obligations%20under%20Corporate%20Social%20Responsibility%20(CSR)%20and%20Environmental%2C%20Social%2C%20and%20Governance%20(ESG).%20They%20can%20also%20be%20exchanged%20to%20meet%20compensatory%20afforestation%20requirements%20under%20the%20Forest%20(Conservation)%20Act%2C%20which%20makes%20it%20mandatory%20for%20project%20developers%20to%20raise%20plantations%20at%20an%20alternate%20site%20for%20cutting%20down%20trees%20on%20forest%20land.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3ELaunched%20in%20October%202023%2C%20the%20Green%20Credit%20Programme%20aims%20to%20create%20tradable%20credits%20from%20a%20range%20of%20activities%2C%20such%20as%20reducing%20air%20pollution%20and%20incorporating%20sustainable%20infrastructure.%20The%20Ministry%20had%20sped%20up%20the%20process%20of%20officiating%20the%20scheme%20by%C2%A0%3Ca%20rel%3D%5C%22noopener%20external%20noreferrer%5C%22%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fimgs.mongabay.com%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2Fsites%2F30%2F2024%2F03%2F19121507%2FCutting-down-window.pdf%5C%22%20data-wpel-link%3D%5C%22external%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Ecutting%20down%3C%2Fa%3E%C2%A0the%20window%20for%20civil%20society%20and%20others%20to%20submit%20their%20objections%20and%20suggestions%20to%20the%20scheme.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%E2%80%9CThe%20Green%20Credit%20Programme%20is%20trying%20to%20do%20some%20pioneering%20work%20on%20inter-sector%20fungibility%2C%20and%20to%20build%20a%20national%20market%20in%20which%20there%20is%20fungibility%20in%20green%20actions.%20This%20is%20important%20because%20what%20we%E2%80%99re%20trying%20to%20do%20is%20create%20equivalence%20and%20deliver%20the%20same%20value%20to%20various%20actors%2C%E2%80%9D%20said%20Swapan%20Mehra%2C%20founder%20and%20CEO%20of%20IORA%20Ecological%20solutions%2C%20an%20environmental%20consultancy%20firm%20that%20helped%20design%20and%20conceptualise%20the%20Green%20Credit%20Programme.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%E2%80%9CWith%20tree%20planting%2C%20even%20if%20initially%20it%20is%20linked%20to%20forest%20department%20lands%20and%20regulations%20like%20CSR%2C%20the%20long-term%20goal%20is%20to%20incentivise%20these%20contributions%20voluntarily%2C%20so%20that%20entities%20want%20to%20contribute%20towards%20sustainability%2C%E2%80%9D%20he%20added.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EA%20new%20Green%20Credit%C2%A0%3Ca%20rel%3D%5C%22noopener%20external%20noreferrer%5C%22%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.moefcc-gcp.in%2F%5C%22%20data-wpel-link%3D%5C%22external%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Ewebsite%3C%2Fa%3E%C2%A0set%20up%20by%20the%20government%20says%20there%20are%20already%20267%20%E2%80%9Cregistered%20plantation%20blocks%E2%80%9D%2C%20amounting%20to%20over%2017%2C000%20hectares%20of%20land%20available%20for%20tree%20planting%2C%20as%20on%20March%2018.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20government%20has%20plans%20of%C2%A0%3Ca%20rel%3D%5C%22noopener%20external%20noreferrer%5C%22%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fpib.gov.in%2FPressReleaseIframePage.aspx%3FPRID%3D1981719%5C%22%20data-wpel-link%3D%5C%22external%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Eshowcasing%3C%2Fa%3E%C2%A0its%20leadership%20with%20the%20Green%20Credit%20Programme%20on%20an%20international%20stage%2C%20with%20the%C2%A0%3Ca%20rel%3D%5C%22noopener%20external%20noreferrer%5C%22%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fggci-world.in%2F%5C%22%20data-wpel-link%3D%5C%22external%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3EGlobal%20Green%20Credit%20Initiative.%C2%A0%3C%2Fa%3EHowever%2C%20the%20initiative%20has%20raised%20several%20concerns%20domestically.%20Experts%20Mongabay%20India%20spoke%20to%20raised%20concerns%20about%20the%20environmental%20soundness%20of%20the%20scheme%2C%20as%20well%20as%20possible%20regulatory%20gaps%20that%20the%20tree%20planting%20methodology%20doesn%E2%80%99t%20directly%20address.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cstrong%3EDeparture%20from%20draft%20guidelines%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20final%20methodology%20to%20generate%20green%20credits%20through%20tree%20planting%20departs%20significantly%20from%20its%C2%A0%3Ca%20rel%3D%5C%22noopener%20external%20noreferrer%5C%22%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fimgs.mongabay.com%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2Fsites%2F30%2F2024%2F03%2F19121619%2FDraft-methodology-Oct-2023.pdf%5C%22%20data-wpel-link%3D%5C%22external%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Edraft%20version%3C%2Fa%3E%2C%20which%20included%20more%20details%20about%20how%20the%20scheme%20would%20operate.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EAccording%20to%20the%20final%20methodology%2C%20forest%20and%20state%20departments%20will%20identify%20and%20%E2%80%9Cmake%20available%E2%80%9D%20degraded%20land%2C%20open%20forests%2C%20scrub%20lands%2C%20wastelands%20and%20catchment%20areas%20for%20large-scale%20tree%20plantations.%20Each%20tree%20planted%20on%20such%20land%20generates%20one%20credit%20and%20the%20minimum%20area%20of%20land%20eligible%20under%20the%20scheme%20is%20five%20hectares.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EParticipants%20must%20pay%20the%20forest%20department%20to%20raise%20the%20plantations%20and%20credits%20will%20be%20issued%20by%20the%20Indian%20Council%20of%20Forestry%20Research%20and%20Education%20(ICFRE)%20after%20the%20plantations%20are%20evaluated.%20The%20methodology%20does%20not%20describe%20the%20criteria%20that%20the%20plantations%20will%20need%20to%20meet%20in%20order%20to%20secure%20approval%2C%20only%20that%20it%20must%20hold%201100%20trees%20per%20hectare%20of%20land%2C%20which%20some%20ecologists%C2%A0%3Ca%20rel%3D%5C%22noopener%20external%20noreferrer%5C%22%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Ffrontline.thehindu.com%2Fenvironment%2Fgreen-credits-where-they-are-due%2Farticle67870309.ece%5C%22%20data-wpel-link%3D%5C%22external%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Ehave%20said%3C%2Fa%3E%C2%A0may%20exacerbate%20degradation.%20Mehra%20agreed%20the%20stipulation%20on%20density%20of%20saplings%20per%20hectare%20could%20be%20less%20stringent.%20%E2%80%9CThe%20number%20of%20saplings%20per%20location%20should%20be%20allowed%20to%20be%20slightly%20flexible%2C%20because%20in%20some%20cases%2C%20putting%201100%20per%20hectare%20might%20be%20difficult%20for%20certain%20types%20of%20species%20and%20land%20types.%E2%80%9D%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20final%20methodology%20leaves%20out%20several%20details%20that%20were%20incorporated%20in%20the%20original%20draft%2C%20which%20laid%20an%20emphasis%20on%20contributions%20of%20individuals%2C%20co-operatives%20and%20small%20land-holding%20farmers.%20The%20draft%20had%20proposed%20the%20credits%20be%20issued%20progressively%20over%2010%20years%2C%20depending%20on%20the%20survivability%20of%20the%20plants%20as%20well%20as%20evidence%20of%20their%20maturation.%20It%20also%20suggested%20the%20minimum%20number%20of%20trees%20planted%20per%20hectare%20be%20100%2C%20and%20the%20maximum%201000.%20The%20draft%20methodology%20even%20considered%20issuing%20credits%20on%20a%20gradient%20across%20different%20rainfall%20zones%2C%20with%20a%20list%20of%20appropriate%20forestry%20and%20horticulture%20species%20that%20can%20be%20planted.%20None%20of%20these%20details%2C%20however%2C%20made%20it%20to%20the%20final%20version.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%E2%80%9CThe%20methodology%20uses%20a%20tree-for-tree%20approach%20without%20considering%20the%20cultural%20importance%20or%20ecosystem%20services%20provided%20by%20forests%20and%20land%2C%E2%80%9D%20said%20Meenakshi%20Kapoor%2C%20an%20independent%20environmental%20researcher%20who%20closely%20tracks%20changes%20to%20India%E2%80%99s%20environmental%20norms.%20The%20newly%20launched%20Green%20Credit%20website%20says%20the%20credits%C2%A0%3Ca%20rel%3D%5C%22external%20noopener%20noreferrer%5C%22%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fmoefcc-gcpregistry.in%2Fresources%2Fmethodologies%5C%22%20data-wpel-link%3D%5C%22external%5C%22%3Ewill%20be%20issued%20within%20two%20years%3C%2Fa%3E%C2%A0of%20the%20forest%20department%20completing%20the%20plantation%20%E2%80%93%20a%20detail%20that%20doesn%E2%80%99t%20find%20mention%20in%20the%20final%20notified%20methodology.%20%E2%80%9CHow%20will%20these%20plantations%20survive%20in%20the%20long%20term%3F%20The%20methodology%20doesn%E2%80%99t%20address%20this%2C%E2%80%9D%20Kapoor%20added.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cfigure%20class%3D%5C%22wp-caption%5C%22%3E%3Cimg%20sizes%3D%5C%22(max-width%3A%201024px)%20100vw%2C%201024px%5C%22%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fimgs.mongabay.com%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2Fsites%2F30%2F2024%2F03%2F18150628%2FWomen_planting_trees_Umaria_district_MP_India.jpg%5C%22%20alt%3D%5C%22%5C%22%20width%3D%5C%221024%5C%22%20srcset%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fimgs.mongabay.com%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2Fsites%2F30%2F2024%2F03%2F18150628%2FWomen_planting_trees_Umaria_district_MP_India.jpg%201024w%2C%20https%3A%2F%2Fimgs.mongabay.com%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2Fsites%2F30%2F2024%2F03%2F18150628%2FWomen_planting_trees_Umaria_district_MP_India-768x577.jpg%20768w%2C%20https%3A%2F%2Fimgs.mongabay.com%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2Fsites%2F30%2F2024%2F03%2F18150628%2FWomen_planting_trees_Umaria_district_MP_India-610x458.jpg%20610w%5C%22%20class%3D%5C%22wp-image-26984%5C%22%20height%3D%5C%22769%5C%22%3E%3Cfigcaption%20class%3D%5C%22wp-caption-text%5C%22%3ECredits%20generated%20through%20tree-planting%20can%20be%20exchanged%20to%20meet%20obligations%20under%20CSR%20and%20ESG.%C2%A0%3Ca%20rel%3D%5C%22noopener%20external%20noreferrer%5C%22%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fcommons.wikimedia.org%2Fwiki%2FFile%3AWomen_planting_trees%2C_Umaria_district%2C_MP%2C_India.jpg%5C%22%20data-wpel-link%3D%5C%22external%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3EPhoto%3C%2Fa%3E%C2%A0by%20Yann%20(talk)%2FWikimedia%20Commons.%3C%2Ffigcaption%3E%3C%2Ffigure%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3ELarge-scale%20plantation%20programmes%2C%20managed%20by%20state%20forest%20departments%2C%20have%20been%20marred%20by%20poor%20monitoring%20and%20compliance.%20An%C2%A0%3Ca%20rel%3D%5C%22noopener%20external%20noreferrer%5C%22%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fscroll.in%2Farticle%2F1014823%2Findias-ghost-plantations-in-which-millions-of-rupees-have-been-sunk%5C%22%20data-wpel-link%3D%5C%22external%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Einvestigation%3C%2Fa%3E%C2%A0into%20state%20afforestation%20programmes%20by%20news%20website%20Scroll%20found%20that%20several%20plantations%20existed%20only%20on%20paper.%20A%202013%C2%A0%3Ca%20rel%3D%5C%22noopener%20external%20noreferrer%5C%22%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fcag.gov.in%2Fen%2Faudit-report%2Fdetails%2F2699%5C%22%20data-wpel-link%3D%5C%22external%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Ereport%3C%2Fa%3E%C2%A0by%20the%20Comptroller%20Auditor%20General%20(CAG)%20also%20noted%20serious%20discrepancies%20in%20compensatory%20afforestation%20efforts%20by%20states.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EIn%20a%20letter%20issued%20on%20March%2019%2C%20a%20group%20of%2091%20retired%20civil%20servants%20wrote%20to%20the%20MOEFCC%20calling%20the%20scheme%20%E2%80%9Cunscientific.%E2%80%9D%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%E2%80%9CCompensatory%20afforestation%20plantations%20already%20undertaken%20in%20our%20country%20are%20known%20to%20have%20dubious%20success%20rates.%20At%20any%20rate%2C%20the%20government%20also%20has%20huge%20unspent%20funds%20for%20such%20afforestation%20programmes%20and%20does%20not%20need%20further%20investment%20from%20any%20private%20agency.%20It%20would%20be%20a%20much%20better%20plan%20to%20merely%20protect%20and%20restore%20these%20degraded%20lands%20to%20their%20original%20condition%2C%E2%80%9D%20the%20civil%20servants%20wrote%20in%20their%20letter%2C%20shared%20with%20the%20media.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cstrong%3ELinks%20to%20the%20carbon%20market%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20Green%20Credit%20Programme%20will%20run%20parallel%20to%20the%20domestic%20carbon%20market%2C%20but%20the%20rules%20suggest%20that%20some%20activities%20can%20be%20shared%20by%20both%20green%20credits%20and%20carbon%20credits.%20Since%20activities%20generating%20green%20credits%20%E2%80%9Cmay%20have%20climate%20co-benefits%E2%80%A6an%20activity%20generating%20green%20credit%20under%20Green%20Credit%20programme%20may%20also%20get%20carbon%20credit%20from%20the%20same%20activity%2C%E2%80%9D%20the%C2%A0%3Ca%20rel%3D%5C%22noopener%20external%20noreferrer%5C%22%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fegazette.gov.in%2FWriteReadData%2F2023%2F249377.pdf%5C%22%20data-wpel-link%3D%5C%22external%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Erules%20say.%3C%2Fa%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EExperts%20say%20that%20the%20Green%20Credit%20Programme%E2%80%99s%20intended%20linkages%20with%20India%E2%80%99s%20upcoming%20carbon%20market%2C%20as%20well%20as%20its%20applicability%20to%20compensatory%20afforestation%20requirements%2C%20could%20prove%20to%20be%20tenuous%20without%20rigorous%20regulations.%20The%C2%A0%3Ca%20rel%3D%5C%22noopener%20external%20noreferrer%5C%22%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fpib.gov.in%2FPressReleasePage.aspx%3FPRID%3D1923458%23%3A~%3Atext%3DTo%2520facilitate%2520the%2520achievement%2520of%2Cby%25202030%2520against%25202005%2520levels.%5C%22%20data-wpel-link%3D%5C%22external%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Eobjective%3C%2Fa%3E%C2%A0of%20India%E2%80%99s%20domestic%20carbon%20market%20is%20to%20reduce%20carbon%20emissions%20from%20key%20sectors.%20Trees%20and%20forests%20have%20a%20potential%20role%20to%20play%20by%20acting%20as%20carbon%20sinks%20that%20absorb%20and%20store%20carbon.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%E2%80%9CWithout%20proper%20regulation%2C%20it%20could%20turn%20into%20a%20problem%20of%20additionality%20in%20the%20carbon%20market%2C%E2%80%9D%20Trishant%20Dev%2C%20programme%20officer%20of%20climate%20change%20at%20the%20Centre%20for%20Science%20and%20Environment%20and%20co-author%20of%20the%20report%C2%A0%3Ca%20rel%3D%5C%22noopener%20external%20noreferrer%5C%22%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.cseindia.org%2Fdiscredited-the-voluntary-carbon-market-in-india-11873%5C%22%20data-wpel-link%3D%5C%22external%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3EDiscredited%3C%2Fa%3E%2C%20which%20investigated%20the%20operations%20of%20the%20international%20voluntary%20carbon%20market%20in%20the%20country%2C%20told%20Mongabay%20India.%20In%20carbon%20markets%2C%20%E2%80%9Cadditionality%E2%80%9D%20refers%20to%20the%20assurance%20that%20emissions%20reductions%2C%20achieved%20through%20the%20sale%20of%20carbon%20credits%2C%20would%20not%20have%20happened%20without%20financial%20support%20from%20those%20credits.%20%E2%80%9CIf%20an%20activity%20has%20already%20been%20compensated%20for%20through%20the%20exchange%20of%20green%20credits%2C%20the%20question%20then%20is%2C%20how%20can%20the%20same%20activity%20be%20compensated%20for%20by%20another%20entity%20in%20exchange%20for%20carbon%20credits%3F%20It%20would%20be%20a%20violation%20of%20the%20principle%20of%20additionality%2C%E2%80%9D%20Dev%20explained.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EMehra%20says%20the%20Green%20Credit%20Scheme%20doesn%E2%80%99t%20support%20double%20counting%2C%20but%20encourages%20%E2%80%9Cdouble%20claiming%2C%E2%80%9D%20as%20a%20way%20of%20enhancing%20the%20monetary%20value%20of%20planting%20trees%2C%20particularly%20for%20small%20land-holders%20who%20have%20not%20had%20access%20to%20the%20carbon%20market%20due%20to%20high%20transaction%20costs.%20%E2%80%9CDouble%20claiming%20is%20when%20you%20can%20claim%20multiple%20forms%20of%20payment%20for%20different%20services%20rendered%20by%20the%20same%20asset.%20This%20is%20different%20from%20double%20counting%2C%20where%20the%20same%20commodity%20is%20sold%20twice%2C%E2%80%9D%20he%20said%2C%20adding%2C%20%E2%80%9CThere%20cannot%20be%20double%20counting%20because%20the%20Green%20Credit%20Programme%20doesn%E2%80%99t%20monetise%20carbon.%20On%20additionality%2C%20existing%20carbon%20market%20standards%20require%20that%20the%20project%20not%20be%20part%20of%20any%20other%20markets%2C%20in%20which%20case%20the%20landowner%20can%20see%20which%2C%20carbon%20credits%20or%20green%20credits%2C%20gives%20them%20higher%20value.%20The%20cash%20flows%20of%20a%20project%20will%20also%20reveal%20how%20much%20was%20funded%20by%20the%20green%20credit%20programme%2C%20and%20if%20it%20exceeds%20the%20threshold%20of%20the%20requirements%20in%20the%20carbon%20market%2C%20it%20can%20be%20deemed%20non-additional.%E2%80%9D%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EMehra%20believes%20that%20as%20the%20programme%20evolves%2C%20a%20distinction%20will%20emerge%20between%20green%20credits%20generated%20on%20forest%20department%20land%20and%20community-owned%20land%2C%20with%20differing%20implications%20on%20additionality.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cfigure%20class%3D%5C%22wp-caption%5C%22%3E%3Cimg%20sizes%3D%5C%22(max-width%3A%201024px)%20100vw%2C%201024px%5C%22%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fimgs.mongabay.com%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2Fsites%2F30%2F2024%2F03%2F18151042%2FAfforestation_status_in_Bhujbas_area_WTK20150923-DSC00240.jpg%5C%22%20alt%3D%5C%22%5C%22%20width%3D%5C%221024%5C%22%20srcset%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fimgs.mongabay.com%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2Fsites%2F30%2F2024%2F03%2F18151042%2FAfforestation_status_in_Bhujbas_area_WTK20150923-DSC00240.jpg%201024w%2C%20https%3A%2F%2Fimgs.mongabay.com%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2Fsites%2F30%2F2024%2F03%2F18151042%2FAfforestation_status_in_Bhujbas_area_WTK20150923-DSC00240-768x576.jpg%20768w%2C%20https%3A%2F%2Fimgs.mongabay.com%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2Fsites%2F30%2F2024%2F03%2F18151042%2FAfforestation_status_in_Bhujbas_area_WTK20150923-DSC00240-610x458.jpg%20610w%5C%22%20class%3D%5C%22wp-image-26985%5C%22%20height%3D%5C%22768%5C%22%3E%3Cfigcaption%20class%3D%5C%22wp-caption-text%5C%22%3EGreen%20credits%20through%20tree%20planting%20can%20also%20be%20exchanged%20to%20meet%20compensatory%20afforestation%20requirements.%C2%A0%3Ca%20rel%3D%5C%22noopener%20external%20noreferrer%5C%22%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fcommons.wikimedia.org%2Fwiki%2FFile%3AAfforestation_status_in_Bhujbas_area_WTK20150923-DSC00240.jpg%5C%22%20data-wpel-link%3D%5C%22external%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3EPhoto%3C%2Fa%3E%C2%A0by%20Dibendu%20Nandi%2FWikimedia%20Commons.%3C%2Ffigcaption%3E%3C%2Ffigure%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20methodology%20for%20tree%20planting%20also%20says%20green%20credits%20generated%20%E2%80%9Cmay%20be%20exchanged%20for%20meeting%20the%20compliance%20of%20the%20compensatory%20afforestation%2C%E2%80%9D%20under%20the%20Forest%20(Conservation)%20Act.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EIn%202022%2C%20the%20rules%20for%20compensatory%20afforestation%20were%C2%A0%3Ca%20rel%3D%5C%22noopener%20external%20noreferrer%5C%22%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fforestsclearance.nic.in%2Fwritereaddata%2Fpublic_display%2Fschemes%2F354734717%24Guidelines%252520on%252520Accredited%252520Compensatory%252520Afforestation.pdf%5C%22%20data-wpel-link%3D%5C%22external%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Ealtered%3C%2Fa%3E%C2%A0to%20allow%20private%20entities%20and%20individuals%20to%20raise%20plantations%20and%20sell%20them%20to%20project%20developers%20looking%20to%20compensate%20for%20the%20forest-loss%20caused%20by%20their%20projects.%20These%20plantations%20would%20need%20to%20be%20at%20least%20five%20years%20old%2C%20spread%20across%2010%20hectares%20or%20more%2C%20with%20a%20canopy%20density%20of%2040%25.%20The%20green%20credit%20methodology%20doesn%E2%80%99t%20suggest%20how%20this%20will%20be%20rationalised%20with%20its%20own%20stipulation%20of%20selling%20credits%20two%20years%20after%20the%20plantation%20is%20established.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%E2%80%9CThe%20methods%20don%E2%80%99t%20talk%20about%20who%20will%20bear%20the%20risk%20if%20the%20plantations%20fail.%20If%20a%20credit%20is%20being%20issued%2C%20how%20can%20it%20be%20taken%20back%3F%20The%20methodology%20needs%20to%20make%20the%20question%20of%20who%20will%20bear%20risk%20clear.%E2%80%9D%20said%20Dev.%20%E2%80%9COperating%20both%20a%20carbon%20market%2C%20and%20a%20green%20credit%20market%20will%20require%20a%20sophisticated%20regulatory%20set-up.%20For%20instance%2C%20maintaining%20registries%20and%20then%20also%20ensuring%20that%20there%20is%20some%20interoperability%20between%20them%2C%20so%20there%E2%80%99s%20no%20duplication%2C%E2%80%9D%20he%20added.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cstrong%3EPressure%20on%20%E2%80%98wastelands%E2%80%99%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EEcologists%20have%20long%20questioned%20the%20rationale%20of%20raising%20plantations%20on%C2%A0%3Ca%20rel%3D%5C%22noopener%20noreferrer%5C%22%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Findia.mongabay.com%2F2022%2F12%2Fexplainer-wastelands-or-grasslands-indias-history-with-defining-open-ecosystems%2F%5C%22%20data-wpel-link%3D%5C%22internal%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Edegraded%20land%20and%20other%20open%20landscapes%3C%2Fa%3E.%20In%20a%20recent%C2%A0%3Ca%20rel%3D%5C%22noopener%20external%20noreferrer%5C%22%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Ffrontline.thehindu.com%2Fenvironment%2Fgreen-credits-where-they-are-due%2Farticle67870309.ece%5C%22%20data-wpel-link%3D%5C%22external%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Eop-ed%3C%2Fa%3E%C2%A0about%20the%20green%20credit%20programme%2C%20ecologists%20Anuja%20Malhotra%20and%20Abi%20T.%20Vanak%2C%20with%20Ashoka%20Trust%20for%20Research%20in%20Ecology%20and%20the%20Environment%2C%20wrote%20the%20biogeography%20of%20the%20land%20should%20be%20taken%20into%20consideration%20when%20planning%20plantations.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cfigure%20class%3D%5C%22wp-caption%5C%22%3E%3Cimg%20sizes%3D%5C%22(max-width%3A%201024px)%20100vw%2C%201024px%5C%22%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fimgs.mongabay.com%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2Fsites%2F30%2F2024%2F03%2F18151332%2F1024px-Savanna_grassland_and_scrub_near_Bhavani_ph_04.jpg%5C%22%20alt%3D%5C%22%5C%22%20width%3D%5C%221024%5C%22%20srcset%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fimgs.mongabay.com%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2Fsites%2F30%2F2024%2F03%2F18151332%2F1024px-Savanna_grassland_and_scrub_near_Bhavani_ph_04.jpg%201024w%2C%20https%3A%2F%2Fimgs.mongabay.com%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2Fsites%2F30%2F2024%2F03%2F18151332%2F1024px-Savanna_grassland_and_scrub_near_Bhavani_ph_04-768x576.jpg%20768w%2C%20https%3A%2F%2Fimgs.mongabay.com%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2Fsites%2F30%2F2024%2F03%2F18151332%2F1024px-Savanna_grassland_and_scrub_near_Bhavani_ph_04-610x458.jpg%20610w%5C%22%20class%3D%5C%22wp-image-26986%5C%22%20height%3D%5C%22768%5C%22%3E%3Cfigcaption%20class%3D%5C%22wp-caption-text%5C%22%3ESavannah%20grassland%20at%20the%20foothills%20of%20the%20Nilgiris%20in%20Coimbatore%20district%2C%20Tamil%20Nadu.%C2%A0%3Ca%20rel%3D%5C%22noopener%20external%20noreferrer%5C%22%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fcommons.wikimedia.org%2Fwiki%2FFile%3ASavanna_grassland_and_scrub_near_Bhavani_ph_04.jpg%5C%22%20data-wpel-link%3D%5C%22external%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3EPhoto%3C%2Fa%3E%C2%A0by%20T.%20R.%20Shankar%20Raman%2FWikimedia%20Commons.%3C%2Ffigcaption%3E%3C%2Ffigure%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%E2%80%9CIt%20should%20explicitly%20mention%20the%20measures%20that%20need%20to%20be%20taken%20to%20make%20land%20suitable%20(such%20as%20soil%20restoration)%20and%20must%20safeguard%20against%20the%20removal%20of%20existing%20natural%20vegetation.%20It%20should%20also%20ensure%20that%20natural%20ecosystems%20such%20as%20savanna%20grasslands%2C%20marshes%2C%20scrub%20forests%2C%20deserts%2C%20rocky%20outcrops%20and%20glades%2C%20which%20are%20currently%20misclassified%20and%20viewed%20as%20non-productive%2Fmarginal%20systems%2C%20are%20not%20harmed%2C%E2%80%9D%20they%20wrote.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3ETree%20plantations%20on%20arid%20land%20have%20also%20proven%20to%20be%20expensive%20with%20poor%20survival%20rates%C2%A0%3Ca%20rel%3D%5C%22noopener%20noreferrer%5C%22%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Findia.mongabay.com%2F2022%2F05%2Fwrong-trees-in-wrong-places-wastes-tree-plantation-budget-finds-study%2F%5C%22%20data-wpel-link%3D%5C%22internal%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Ein%20states%20like%20Himachal%20Pradesh%3C%2Fa%3E%2C%20where%20incorrect%20species%20are%20planted%20on%20unviable%20land%20parcels.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%E2%80%9CRestoration%20efforts%20tend%20to%20target%20sites%20that%20are%20highly%20degraded%2C%20in%20terms%20of%20both%20ecosystem%20structure%20and%20floristic%20composition%2C%20while%20sites%20that%20appear%20less%20degraded%2C%20at%20least%20in%20terms%20of%20structure%2C%20receive%20less%20attention%2C%E2%80%9D%20said%20Anand%20Osuri%2C%20a%20researcher%20with%20the%20Nature%20Conservation%20Foundation%20(NCF)%20who%20works%20on%20eco-restoration.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3ENew%C2%A0%3Ca%20rel%3D%5C%22noopener%20external%20noreferrer%5C%22%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.sciencedirect.com%2Fscience%2Farticle%2Fabs%2Fpii%2FS0006320724000806%3Fdgcid%3Dauthor%5C%22%20data-wpel-link%3D%5C%22external%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Eresearch%3C%2Fa%3E%C2%A0by%20NCF%20from%20the%20Western%20Ghats%20shows%20that%20even%20these%20seemingly%20less-degraded%20forests%20can%20prove%20to%20be%20important%20arenas%20for%20restoration.%20Their%20study%20suggests%20that%20such%20forests%20offer%20substantial%20opportunities%20for%20broadening%20restoration%20efforts%2C%20conserving%20threatened%20tree%20species%2C%20and%20enhancing%20long-term%20carbon%20storage.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%E2%80%9CFocusing%20more%20on%20such%20forests%20for%20restoration%20can%20reduce%20the%20demand%20on%20agricultural%20lands%20and%20open%20natural%20ecosystems%20for%20meeting%20restoration%20targets%20and%20it%20can%20create%20opportunities%20for%20restoring%20forest-specialist%20species%2C%E2%80%9D%20Osuri%20added.%3C%2Fp%3E%22%2C%22published%22%3A1711017024000%2C%22visual%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fcdn.thewire.in%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2F2024%2F03%2F21135439%2FAfforestation_status_in_Bhujbas_area_WTK20150923-DSC00240.jpg%22%2C%22originID%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fthewire.in%2Fenvironment%2Fenvironment-experts-question-govts-green-credit-scheme-say-methodology-doesnt-inspire-confidence%22%2C%22summary%22%3A%22The%20final%20methodology%20to%20generate%20green%20credits%20through%20tree%20planting%20departs%20significantly%20from%20its%C2%A0draft%20version%2C%20which%20included%20more%20details%20about%20how%20the%20scheme%20would%20operate.%22%2C%22author%22%3A%22%22%2C%22engagement%22%3A0%2C%22canonicalUrl%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fthewire.in%2Fenvironment%2Fenvironment-experts-question-govts-green-credit-scheme-say-methodology-doesnt-inspire-confidence%22%2C%22cdnAmpUrl%22%3A%22%22%2C%22ampUrl%22%3A%22%22%7D%2C%7B%22title%22%3A%22Dollar%20General%20is%20taking%20a%20key%20strategy%20from%20Costco%20as%20it%20aims%20to%20lower%20costs%22%2C%22content%22%3A%22%3Cfigure%3E%3Cimg%20width%3D%5C%223750%5C%22%20alt%3D%5C%22A%20black-and-yellow%20Dollar%20General%20sign%20hangs%20above%20a%20store%20in%20Maryland%20as%20seen%20from%20between%20yellow%20shopping%20carts%20in%20the%20parking%20lot.%5C%22%20charset%3D%5C%22%5C%22%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fi.insider.com%2F65a7ecf843bb77284b9db495%3Fformat%3Djpeg%5C%22%20height%3D%5C%222500%5C%22%3E%3Cfigcaption%3EDollar%20General%20is%20cutting%20back%20its%20product%20selection%20to%20simplify%20operations%20at%20its%20stores.%3Cp%3EERIN%20SCOTT%2FReuters%3C%2Fp%3E%3C%2Ffigcaption%3E%3C%2Ffigure%3E%3Cul%3E%3Cli%3EDollar%20General%20is%20sharply%20reducing%20the%20selection%20of%20products%20it%20sells%20in%20order%20to%20cut%20costs.%3C%2Fli%3E%3Cli%3EThe%20discounter%20previously%20stocked%20about%2012%2C000%20unique%20items%2C%20referenced%20by%20SKUs.%3C%2Fli%3E%3Cli%3E%3Cstrong%3EThe%C2%A0strategy%20%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Ffounding-history-of-costco%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3E%3Cstrong%3Ehas%20worked%20well%20for%20Costco%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fa%3E%3Cstrong%3E.%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fli%3E%3C%2Ful%3E%3Cp%3ESome%20Dollar%20General%20shoppers%20may%20see%20their%20favorite%20items%20disappearing%20from%20shelves%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fdollar-general-replacing-some-self-checkouts-because-of-theft-shrink-2024-3%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Eas%20the%20discount%20retailer%20looks%20to%20control%20inventory%20costs%3C%2Fa%3E.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20company%20said%20last%20week%20that%20it%20is%20slashing%20as%20many%20as%201%2C000%20unique%20items%2C%20referenced%20by%20stock%20keeping%20units%20(SKUs)%2C%20from%20its%20product%20line-up.%20Exact%20counts%20vary%20by%20location%2C%20but%20the%20company%20previously%20said%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fdollar-general-low-price-strategy-2018-8%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Emost%20stores%20tend%20to%20carry%20around%2011%2C000%20to%2012%2C000%20SKUs%3C%2Fa%3E.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EAs%20a%20so-called%20%26quot%3Blimited%20selection%26quot%3B%20retailer%2C%20Dollar%20General's%20count%20is%20a%20mere%20fraction%20of%20the%20typical%20US%20supermarket%2C%20which%20offers%20about%2030%2C000%20to%2040%2C000%2C%20or%20a%20Walmart%20Supercenter%2C%20which%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Finventory-management.com%2Finventory-management%2Finventory-management-at-walmart%2F%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Ereportedly%3C%2Fa%3E%20carries%20more%20than%20140%2C000%20items.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20move%20inches%20Dollar%20General%20closer%20to%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fwhat-the-costco-star-of-death-means-2023-7%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3ECostco's%20time-tested%20strategy%3C%2Fa%3E%20for%20finding%20savings%20through%20simplicity%20%E2%80%94%20the%20wholesale%20club%20famously%20keeps%20its%20SKU%20count%20to%20around%204%2C000%20in%20its%20warehouses.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3ECEO%20Todd%20Vasos%20hinted%20at%20how%20this%20looks%20in%20practice%20when%20he%20previewed%20the%20move%20in%20Dollar%20General's%20earnings%20call%20last%20December.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BWe%20may%20have%20five%20or%20six%20different%20variants%20of%20mayonnaise%20on%20the%20shelf%20today%2C%26quot%3B%20he%20said.%20%26quot%3BWe%20can%20easily%20drop%20one%20or%20two%20of%20those.%20The%20consumer%20is%20not%20going%20to%20know%20the%20difference.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EBecause%20each%20flavor%2C%20color%2C%20or%20size%20of%20a%20product%20requires%20a%20unique%20SKU%2C%20there's%20often%20a%20fair%20amount%20of%20room%20for%20retailers%20to%20focus%20on%20a%20crowd%20favorite%20and%20skip%20the%20hassle%20of%20trying%20to%20match%20everyone's%20unique%20preferences.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3ESimplifying%20the%20selection%20also%20can%20drive%20more%20sales%20toward%20higher%20volume%20items%2C%20which%20can%20improve%20economies%20of%20scale%2C%20GlobalData%20retail%20analyst%20Neil%20Saunders%20told%20Business%20Insider.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BLow%20SKU%20counts%20with%20high%20volumes%20is%20a%20model%20that%20serves%20a%20lot%20of%20price-focused%20retailers%20very%20well%2C%26quot%3B%20he%20said.%20%26quot%3BCostco%20uses%20this%2C%20as%20does%20Aldi.%20It's%20all%20about%20leveraging%20efficiency%20to%20reduce%20costs%20which%20enables%20lower%20prices.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EAt%20the%20same%20time%2C%20retailers%20need%20to%20make%20cuts%20with%20care%20to%20make%20sure%20they%20don't%20eliminate%20items%20that%20customers%20are%20especially%20fond%20of.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EIn%20fact%2C%20fewer%20options%20may%20come%20as%20a%20relief%20to%20some%20shoppers%20suffering%20from%20decision%20fatigue%2C%20as%20any%20Costco%20diehard%20will%20tell%20you.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EAnd%20as%20Costco%20shows%2C%20retailers%20can%20still%20offer%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fwhat-to-buy-at-costco-according-to-superfans-2023-12%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Ea%20staggering%20range%20of%20product%20categories%3C%2Fa%3E%20without%20loading%20up%20on%20an%20infinite%20variety%20within%20particular%20products%20themselves.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20benefits%20of%20simplifying%20the%20selection%20also%20extend%20to%20store%20staff%20and%20the%20company's%20distribution%20teams%2C%20Vasos%20said%2C%20since%20that's%20one%20less%20product%20that%20has%20to%20be%20shipped%2C%20tracked%2C%20and%20stocked%20on%20a%20shelf.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThat%20simplification%20could%20boost%20the%20retailer's%20efforts%20to%20clean%20up%20its%20stores%3A%20Some%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fdollar-general-stores-closing-fire-code-violations-too-much-stuff-2023-2%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3EDollar%20General%20locations%20have%20been%20awash%20in%20unpacked%20inventory%3C%2Fa%3E%2C%20creating%20fire%20hazards%20and%20a%20nightmare%20for%20overworked%20employees.%20Some%20workers%20told%20BI%20that%20their%20stores%20were%20filled%20with%20Christmas%20decorations%2C%20dog%20food%2C%20and%20other%20products%20that%20weren't%20selling%20as%20fast%20as%20Dollar%20General's%20distribution%20centers%20were%20sending%20them%20to%20stores.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3ELast%20summer%2C%20Dollar%20General%20took%20a%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fdollar-general-takes-action-messy-overstocked-stores-marks-down-items-2023-8%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3E%2495%20million%20inventory%20write-down%3C%2Fa%3E%20as%20it%20cleaned%20those%20stores%20up.%20It%20also%20invested%20more%20in%20worker%20pay%20to%20help.%20Analysts%20have%20pointed%20to%20the%20clutter%20as%20one%20factor%20weighing%20on%20the%20company's%20financial%20results.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3ESupply%20chain%20snafus%20during%20the%20pandemic%20threw%20a%20spotlight%20on%20the%20expense%20associated%20with%20offering%20a%20seemingly%20infinite%20array%20of%20consumer%20choices%2C%20and%20companies%20are%20still%20looking%20for%20ways%20to%20ensure%20that%20shoppers%20are%20buying%20enough%20of%20something%20to%20make%20it%20worth%20selling.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3ESeveral%20major%20consumer%20products%20companies%20have%20said%20in%20recent%20months%20that%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fwhy-shoppers-will-see-fewer-options-on-shelves-in-2024-2024-1%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Eshoppers%20didn't%20really%20notice%3C%2Fa%3E%20a%20lot%20of%20the%20items%20they%20stopped%20selling%20during%20the%20pandemic.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EMore%20recently%2C%20Hasbro%20%E2%80%94%20the%20make