%2F65075c23cd637c0019c68cf8%3Fformat%3Djpeg%5C%22%20height%3D%5C%223551%5C%22%3E%3Cfigcaption%3EUnited%20Auto%20Workers%20members%20march%20through%20downtown%20Detroit%20on%20September%2015%2C%202023.%3Cp%3EAP%20Photo%2FPaul%20Sancya%3C%2Fp%3E%3C%2Ffigcaption%3E%3C%2Ffigure%3E%3Cul%3E%3Cli%3EUnion%20households%20have%20a%20significantly%20higher%20median%20wealth%20than%20nonunion%20families%2C%20Fed%20data%20showed.%3C%2Fli%3E%3Cli%3EBeing%20in%20a%20union%20also%20helps%20to%20reduce%20racial%20and%20educational%20wealth%20gaps.%3C%2Fli%3E%3Cli%3EHowever%2C%20union%20membership%20rates%20have%20been%20declining%20for%20years%20and%20hit%20a%20record%20low%20in%202023.%3C%2Fli%3E%3C%2Ful%3E%3Cp%3EIt%20pays%20to%20be%20in%20a%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Funion-definition-why-companies-amazon-oppose-labor-organizing-workers-rights-2021-3%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Eunion%3C%2Fa%3E%2C%20according%20to%20a%20new%20analysis%20of%20Americans'%20household%20finances.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20Center%20for%20American%20Progress%2C%20a%20left-leaning%20think%20tank%2C%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.americanprogress.org%2Farticle%2Funions-continue-to-build-wealth-for-all-americans%2F%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Elooked%3C%2Fa%3E%20at%20just%20how%20much%20better%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fmiddle-class-workers-falling-behind-unions-could-help-biden-administration-2023-8%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Eunion%20workers%20are%20faring%3C%2Fa%3E.%20By%20analyzing%20the%20Federal%20Reserve's%20Survey%20of%20Consumer%20Finances%2C%20CAP%20found%20that%20in%202022%2C%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Flabor-union-approval-hasnt-been-this-high-since-1965-2022-8%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Eunion%20households%3C%2Fa%3E%20held%20%24338%2C482%20in%20median%20wealth.%20Meanwhile%2C%20nonunion%20households%20had%20%24199%2C948.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EBeing%20in%20a%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2F2023-year-of-the-strike-unions-sag-aftra-uaw-2023-12%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Eunion%3C%2Fa%3E%20also%20substantially%20chips%20away%20at%20racial%20and%20educational%20wealth%20gaps%2C%20per%20CAP's%20analysis.%20Black%2C%20nonunion%20households%20have%20a%20median%20household%20wealth%20of%20%2461%2C500%3B%20meanwhile%2C%20Black%20union%20households%20hold%20around%20%24164%2C6000%20in%20median%20household%20wealth.%20Black%20workers%20are%20also%20more%20likely%20than%20workers%20of%20other%20races%20to%20be%20in%20a%20union%2C%20according%20to%20the%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.bls.gov%2Fnews.release%2Funion2.htm%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3EBureau%20of%20Labor%20Statistics%3C%2Fa%3E%2C%20with%20their%20union%20membership%20rates%20outpacing%20their%20white%2C%20Asian%2C%20and%20Hispanic%20counterparts.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EUnions%20particularly%20pay%20off%20for%20workers%20without%20a%20high%20school%20degree%20and%20again%20seem%20to%20be%20bridging%20educational%20wealth%20gaps%2C%20per%20the%20data.%20The%20median%20wealth%20of%20union%20members%20without%20a%20high%20school%20degree%20is%20over%20three%20times%20that%20of%20nonunion%20workers%20without%20a%20high%20school%20degree%20%E2%80%94%20%2469%2C510%20compared%20to%20%2422%2C800%20respectively.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3ESince%20the%20job%20of%20a%20union%20typically%20involves%20negotiating%20higher%20pay%20and%20better%20benefits%20for%20its%20members%2C%20it's%20well-documented%20that%20union%20members%20in%20the%20US%20tend%20to%20make%20more%20than%20their%20nonunionized%20counterparts.%20The%20Bureau%20of%20Labor%20Statistics'%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.bls.gov%2Fnews.release%2Funion2.htm%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Eanalysis%20of%20union%20membership%20in%202023%20found%3C%2Fa%3E%20that%20union%20members%20had%20median%20weekly%20earnings%20of%20%241%2C263%20%E2%80%94%20around%20%2465%2C676%20annually%20%E2%80%94%20compared%20to%20%241%2C090%20for%20nonunion%20workers.%20Per%20the%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.bls.gov%2Fnews.release%2Fpdf%2Fwkyeng.pdf%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3EBureau%20of%20Labor%20Statistics%3C%2Fa%3E%2C%20median%20weekly%20earnings%20for%20all%20workers%20came%20in%20at%20%241%2C145%20in%20the%20last%20quarter%20of%202023.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EResearch%20has%20previously%20found%20that%20union%20membership%20could%20lead%20to%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fbeing-in-union-make-1-million-dollars-more-over-lifetime-2022-10%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Eover%20a%20million%20dollars%3C%2Fa%3E%20more%20in%20lifetime%20earnings.%20Zachary%20Parolin%20of%20Bocconi%20University%20and%20Tom%20VanHeuvelen%20of%20the%20University%20of%20Minnesota%20Twin%20Cities%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fjournals.sagepub.com%2Fdoi%2F10.1177%2F00197939221129261%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Efound%3C%2Fa%3E%20that%20workers%20who%20spent%20their%20whole%20careers%20in%20unions%20saw%20a%20%241.3%20million%20bump%20in%20lifetime%20earnings.%20That%20research%20also%20found%20that%20unions%20can%20help%20bridge%20educational%20wealth%20divides%3A%20Workers%20who%20don't%20have%20a%20college%20degree%20%E2%80%94%20but%20have%20spent%20the%20entirety%20of%20their%20careers%20in%20unions%20%E2%80%94%20were%20actually%20anticipated%20to%20make%20more%20than%20workers%20who%20have%20a%20college%20degree%20but%20are%20not%20in%20a%20union.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EHowever%2C%20those%20wage%20benefits%20are%20restricted%20to%20a%20small%20segment%20of%20workers.%20Union%20membership%20rates%20have%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Flabor-union-membership-fell-lowest-rate-record-2022-2023-1%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Edeclined%20for%20decades%3C%2Fa%3E%2C%20reaching%20a%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.bls.gov%2Fnews.release%2Funion2.htm%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank