ppear%20to%20be%20perking%20up%20as%20well.%3C%2Fp%3E%3C%2Fli%3E%3C%2Ful%3E%3Cul%3E%3Cli%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20US%20is%20importing%20more%20capital%20goods.%20January's%20trade%20data%20indicates%20imports%20of%20real%20capital%20goods%20rose%20by%203.8%25%20month%20over%20month.%20Over%20the%20past%20six%20months%20they've%20increased%20by%209.6%25%20at%20an%20annual%20rate.%20Ultimately%2C%20imported%20capital%20goods%20will%20be%20used%20for%20domestic%20production.%3C%2Fp%3E%3C%2Fli%3E%3C%2Ful%3E%3Cul%3E%3Cli%3E%3Cp%3EStocks%20are%20up.%20A%20rising%20stock%20price%20means%20stronger%20balance%20sheets%20and%20more%20collateral%20against%20which%20to%20borrow.%20So%20during%20a%20boom%2C%20there's%20a%20positive%20feedback%20loop%3A%20Rising%20stock%20prices%20and%20easier%20lending%20standards%20accelerate%20the%20impact%20on%20investment.%3C%2Fp%3E%3C%2Fli%3E%3C%2Ful%3E%3Cp%3ECapital%20spending%20also%20benefits%20from%20an%20accelerator%20effect.%20If%20companies%20perceive%20the%20economy%20as%20getting%20better%2C%20they're%20more%20likely%20to%20spend%20more%20on%20capital%20goods%20to%20meet%20the%20expected%20increase%20in%20demand.%20So%20when%20GDP%20growth%20accelerates%2C%20investment%20tends%20to%20rise%20even%20faster%2C%20which%20should%20push%20up%20productivity%20down%20the%20line.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cdiv%20data-script%3D%5C%22%5C%22%20data-styles%3D%5C%22default-width%5C%22%20data-embed-type%3D%5C%22custom%5C%22%20data-type%3D%5C%22embed%5C%22%3E%3Ciframe%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fdatawrapper.dwcdn.net%2FA1Smd%2F1%2F%5C%22%20title%3D%5C%22Real%20GDP%20vs%20nonresidential%20fixed%20investment%5C%22%20data-external%3D%5C%221%5C%22%20height%3D%5C%22450%5C%22%3E%3C%2Fiframe%3E%3C%2Fdiv%3E%3Cp%3EA%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fjobs-unemployment-work-labor-market-wage-growth-in-february-2024-3%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Esteadying%20of%20the%20labor%20market%3C%2Fa%3E%20is%20also%20a%20strong%20sign%20of%20a%20coming%20productivity%20boom.%20In%20the%20early%20days%20of%20the%20pandemic%2C%20labor%20markets%20were%20red%20hot%2C%20driving%20up%20the%20rate%20of%20quitting%20and%20hiring.%20Employers%20were%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fgreat-resignation-still-going-layoffs-low-job-openings-quits-high-2022-11%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Erunning%20around%20with%20fishnets%3C%2Fa%3E%20trying%20to%20find%20people%2C%20and%20workers%20used%20their%20leverage.%20A%20little%20heat%20in%20the%20job%20market%20is%20good%2C%20but%20you%20can%20have%20too%20much%20of%20a%20good%20thing.%20It's%20hard%20to%20establish%20productivity%20if%20folks%20aren't%20actually%20staying%20in%20their%20positions%20for%20that%20long.%20Today%2C%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fquitting-job-big-stay-great-resignation-labor-market-economic-outlook-2024-1%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Elabor-market%20conditions%20have%20settled%3C%2Fa%3E%3A%20Job%20openings%20have%20declined%2C%20unemployment%20has%20increased%20somewhat%2C%20and%20workers%20are%20less%20willing%20to%20quit%20their%20jobs.%20This%20means%20people%20are%20staying%20in%20their%20jobs%20longer.%20As%20workers%20gain%20experience%20in%20their%20roles%2C%20productivity%20should%20follow.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3ETotal%20factor%20productivity%20has%20been%20particularly%20weak%20since%20the%20start%20of%20the%20pandemic%20%E2%80%94%20perhaps%20innovation%20has%20slowed%20down%20or%20employees%20are%20still%20getting%20used%20to%20new%20in-person%20or%20hybrid%20work%20arrangements%20in%20the%20remote-work%20era.%20But%20those%20hurdles%20should%20fall%20into%20the%20rearview%20mirror%20as%20the%20economy%20settles.%20At%20the%20same%20time%2C%20there%20has%20recently%20been%20a%20burst%20of%20new%20business%20formation.%20That's%20important%20since%20the%20slowing%20pace%20of%20business%20dynamism%20and%20lack%20of%20new%20business%20formation%20in%20the%202000s%20was%20said%20to%20