hanges%20and%20economists%20are%20mismeasuring%20the%20change%20in%20productivity.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EProductivity%20shocks%20tend%20to%20come%20in%20waves.%20The%202010s%2C%20when%20productivity%20consistently%20fell%20short%20of%20expectations%2C%20was%20a%20period%20of%20chronically%20overestimated%20growth%3A%20The%20consensus%20would%20start%20the%20year%20at%20about%203%25%20but%20end%20up%20at%201.5%25%20or%202%25.%20By%20contrast%2C%20the%20late%201990s%20were%20a%20period%20of%20higher%20productivity%20growth%20and%20underestimated%20growth%2C%20starting%20the%20year%20at%202%25%20but%20ending%20closer%20to%204%25.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cdiv%20data-script%3D%5C%22%5C%22%20data-styles%3D%5C%22default-width%5C%22%20data-embed-type%3D%5C%22custom%5C%22%20data-type%3D%5C%22embed%5C%22%3E%3Ciframe%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fdatawrapper.dwcdn.net%2Fpu1Of%2F1%2F%5C%22%20title%3D%5C%22GDP%20growth%20projections%5C%22%20data-external%3D%5C%221%5C%22%20height%3D%5C%22450%5C%22%3E%3C%2Fiframe%3E%3C%2Fdiv%3E%3Cp%3EThese%20historical%20examples%20are%20worth%20thinking%20about%20today%20because%20growth%20expectations%20are%20climbing.%20Blue%20Chip%20consensus%20expectations%20for%202024%20real%20GDP%20have%20jumped%2C%20tripling%20since%20last%20summer%2C%20to%202.1%25%20from%200.7%25%20in%20June.%20Unsurprisingly%2C%20recession%20fears%20have%20collapsed.%20Professional%20forecasters%20now%20see%20just%20a%2023.9%25%20chance%20of%20a%20drop%20in%20real%20GDP%20in%20the%20next%20quarter%2C%20down%20from%20nearly%2050%25%20this%20time%20last%20year.%20If%20we're%20seeing%20a%20genuine%20increase%20in%20productivity%2C%20the%20takeaway%20is%20that%20it's%20unlikely%20to%20be%20fleeting.%20If%20the%20past%20is%20prologue%2C%20the%20consensus%20will%20consistently%20be%20revising%20up%20growth%20estimates.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Ch2%3EThe%20AI%20boom%20isn't%20here%20%E2%80%94%C2%A0yet%3C%2Fh2%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20media%20is%20littered%20with%20discussions%20about%20how%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fai-tackling-jobs-humans-dont-have-time-for-or-want-2024-2%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3EAI%20is%20going%20to%20send%20productivity%3C%2Fa%3E%20into%20hyperspeed.%20But%20it's%20probably%20too%20soon%20to%20be%20thinking%20about%20these%20factors%20as%20the%20main%20driver%20of%20recent%20productivity%20growth.%20That's%20an%20important%20part%20of%20the%20productivity%20paradox.%20Productivity%20miracles%20don't%20necessarily%20follow%20a%20technological%20breakthrough%20right%20away.%20It%20takes%20time%20for%20the%20technology%20to%20make%20its%20way%20through%20the%20economy%20and%20time%20for%20workers%20to%20gain%20the%20skills%20needed%20to%20make%20the%20most%20of%20it.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20good%20news%20is%20that%20the%20normalization%20of%20the%20economy%20%E2%80%94%20improvement%20in%20supply%20chains%2C%20balanced%20labor%20markets%20%E2%80%94%20is%20likely%20to%20result%20in%20continued%20improvement%20in%20business-sector%20productivity%20growth.%20I%20think%20%26quot%3Bnormal%26quot%3B%20is%20about%201.5%25%20to%202%25.%20There's%20likely%20some%20improvement%20on%20the%20horizon%20as%20capital%20spending%20outpaces%20hours%20worked%3B%20as%20a%20result%2C%20we'll%20get%20a%20bit%20more%20capital%20deepening%20this%20year.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20investment%20implications%20of%20this%20are%20clear%3A%20Stronger%20productivity%20growth%20implies%20a%20higher%20speed%20limit%20for%20the%20economy.%20Wages%20can%20grow%20somewhat%20faster%20without%20pressuring%20firms%20to%20raise%20prices%20%E2%80%94%20a%20positive%20development%20for%20the%20Fed%2C%20at%20least%20in%20the%20short%20run.%20On%20the%20flip%20side%2C%20neutral%20rates%20might%20be%20somewhat%20higher%20as%20a%20result.%20For%20stocks%2C%20stronger%20productivity%20should%20be%20welcomed%2C%20implying%20more%20growth%20with%20stronger%20profit%20margins.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Chr%3E%3Cp%3E%3Ca%20rel%3D%5C%22%5C%22%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.c