om%2Fcalifornia-man-wins-second-biggest-powerball-jackpot-ever-2024-3%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Ewin%20the%20lottery%3C%2Fa%3E%20that%20evening%2C%20you%20probably%20won't%20show%20up%20at%20work%20the%20next%20day.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EWe%20all%20play%20the%20game%2C%20and%20sometimes%20that%20means%20exaggerating%20a%20bit.%20But%20there%20are%20three%20things%20that%20you%20should%20absolutely%20never%20lie%20about.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Ch2%3E1.%20Never%20lie%20about%20where%20you've%20worked%20and%20your%20dates%20of%20employment%3C%2Fh2%3E%3Cp%3EA%20background%20check%20will%20list%20the%20employers%20you've%20had%20along%20with%20dates%20of%20employment.%20Padding%20your%20r%C3%A9sum%C3%A9%20to%20hide%20an%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Frecruiters-resume-cv-advice-career-gaps-labor-shortage-great-resignation-2022-1%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Eemployment%20gap%3C%2Fa%3E%20or%20citing%20examples%20from%20places%20you've%20never%20worked%20will%20likely%20raise%20major%20questions%20about%20your%20integrity%20and%20could%20lead%20to%20a%20rescinded%20offer.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EA%20few%20years%20back%2C%20I%20interviewed%20someone%20whose%20r%C3%A9sum%C3%A9%20showed%20two%20years%20of%20experience%20in%20a%20role%20with%20an%20organization%20that%20I%20was%20pretty%20familiar%20with.%20But%20when%20I%20asked%20about%20their%20experiences%2C%20they%20shared%20several%20things%20that%20seemed%20inconsistent%20with%20what%20I%20knew%20about%20the%20organization.%20The%20employer%20didn't%20appear%20on%20their%20LinkedIn%20profile%20either.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EIt%20turned%20out%20they%20had%20worked%20in%20that%20role%20for%20only%20a%20few%20months%20but%20claimed%20to%20have%20held%20the%20position%20for%20a%20few%20years%20to%20show%20more%20relevant%20experience.%20The%20result%20was%20that%20we%20weren't%20interested%20in%20the%20candidate.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Ch3%3EInstead%3A%20List%20every%20employer%20and%20note%20the%20years%20instead%20of%20months%20worked%3C%2Fh3%3E%3Cp%3EList%20every%20employer%20you've%20ever%20worked%20for%2C%20with%20accurate%20dates.%20It's%20OK%20to%20note%20the%20years%20instead%20of%20months%20to%20minimize%20the%20perception%20of%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fgen-z-happy-job-hopping-quit-without-backup-oliver-wyman-2023-1%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Ejob-hopping%3C%2Fa%3E%20if%20needed.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EIf%20you've%20done%20periods%20of%20freelance%20work%2C%20you%20can%20group%20these%20under%20one%20job%20and%20list%20dates%20within%20that%20period%20and%20the%20projects%20you%20worked%20on.%20Doing%20so%20will%20make%20it%20look%20more%20cohesive%20than%20listing%20out%20a%20series%20of%20short-term%20projects.%20You%20can%20name%20the%20companies%20you've%20worked%20with%2C%20but%20don't%20imply%20employment%20if%20it%20was%20simply%20a%20one-off%20short-term%20project.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Ch2%3E2.%20Never%20lie%20about%20your%20references%3C%2Fh2%3E%3Cp%3EWhile%20it%20may%20be%20tempting%20to%20use%20fake%20references%20when%20you're%20not%20confident%20about%20what%20previous%20employers%20will%20share%2C%20it's%20not%20a%20good%20idea.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3ECompanies%20will%20generally%20check%20references%20to%20understand%20the%20projects%20and%20initiatives%20you've%20worked%20on%20and%20how%20you've%20impacted%20the%20business.%20A%20reference%20that%20fails%20to%20clearly%20articulate%20this%20with%20specificity%20may%20cause%20more%20harm%20than%20good.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EI%20once%20met%20someone%20at%20a%20social%20event%20and%20commiserated%20with%20them%20about%20their%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fwhat-to-do-when-you-dont-get-along-with-your-boss-2022-10%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Ebad%20relationship%20with%20their%20manager%3C%2Fa%3E.%20Then%2C%20they%20asked%20me%20if%20I'd%20be%20willing%20to%20be%20a%20fake%20reference%20for%20them%20and%20give%20them%20my%20number%20and%20a%20fake%20email%20to%20pretend%20to%20be%20their%20manager.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EMy%20answer%3F%20No!%20Not%20only%20could%20doing%20this%20potentially%20have%20ramifications%20for%20me%2C%20but%20even%20if%20the%20employer%20never%20caught%20on%2C%20I%20knew%20I%20wouldn't%20be%20able%20to%20speak%20to%20this%20person's%20work%20convincingly.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3ESome%20potential%20red%20flags%20to%20a%20hiring%20manager%20could%20be%20if%20the%20reference's%20LinkedIn%20doesn't%20show%20that%20they%20worked%20at%20the%20same%20company%20as%20you%2C%20or%20if%20all%20of%20your%20references%20have%20personal%20email%20addresses%20instead%20of%20professional%20ones.%20These%20could%20cast%20doubt%20upon%20you%20as%20a%20candidate%20and%20lead%20to%20questions.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EIf%20you%20reach%20the%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Freference-checks-key-to-hiring-extraordinary-people-2013-10%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Ereference%20stage%20with%20a%20potential%20employer%3C%2Fa%3E%2C%20they%20want%20you%20and%20are%20excited%20about%20you.%20The%20references%20are%20simply%20there%20to%20validate%20that%20you%20are%2C%20in%20fact%2C%20a%20great%20match.%20The%20last%20thing%20you%20want%20to%20do%20is%20cast%20doubt%20on%20that%20through%20the%20people%20you%20list%20on%20a%20reference%20check.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Ch3%3EInstead%3A%20Consider%20mentors%20or%20colleagues%20with%20a%20more%20senior%20title%3C%2Fh3%3E%3Cp%3EFirst%2C%20go%20through%20your%20previous%20managers%20and%20department%20leaders%20and%20identify%20those%20you%20know%20were%20your%20fans.%20If%20you%20don't%20have%20a%20past%20manager%20who%20can%20vouch%20for%20you%2C%20consider%20another%20mentor%20or%20person%20with%20a%20more%20senior%20title.%20Select%20a%20few%20peers%20as%20well.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3ELet%20them%20know%20that%20you'd%20like%20to%20use%20them%20as%20a%20reference%2C%20and%20check%20if%20they%20are%20comfortable%20with%20that.%20Provide%20them%20with%20your%20r%C3%A9sum%C3%A9%20and%20highlight%20a%20few%20recent%20achievements.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EEmployers%20will%20generally%20want%20to%20hear%20from%20at%20least%20one%20manager%20and%20other%20stakeholders%20who%20know%20your%20work%20so%20that%20they%20can%20get%20a%20more%20well-rounded%20view%20of%20your%20impact.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Ch2%3E3.%20Never%20lie%20about%20your%20hard%20skills%3C%2Fh2%3E%3Cp%3EWe%20know%20that%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fmarkets.businessinsider.com%2Fnews%2Fstocks%2Fdespite-recruiter-confidence-exaggeration-and-skills-gaps-plague-the-hiring-process-1028619165%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Eeveryone%20exaggerates%20a%20bit%3C%2Fa%3E%20to%20paint%20their%20experiences%20in%20a%20more%20positive%20light.%20But%20you%20should%20never%20completely%20invent%20skills%20or%20claim%20expertise%20in%20an%20area%20with%20which%20you%20have%20no%20experience.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EEven%20if%20you%20land%20the%20job%2C%20the%20truth%20will%20come%20out%20as%20the%20company%20assesses%20skills%20through%20work%20products.%20Not%20having%20the%20necessary%20skills%20could%20lead%20to%20failing%20to%20perform%20well%20and%20damaging%20your%20reputation.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EYou%20might%20even%20find%20yourself%20out%20of%20a%20job%20after%20just%20a%20few%20short%20weeks%20%E2%80%94%20and%20that%20could%20leave%20you%20in%20an%20even%20worse%20situation%20as%20you%20start%20from%20square%20one%20with%20a%20new%20job%20search.%20Meanwhile%2C%20if%20you%20had%20been%20honest%2C%20perhaps%20you%20could've%20been%20considered%20for%20other%20roles%20that%20would've%20actually%20been%20a%20good%20fit.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Ch3%3EInstead%3A%20Build%20on%20skills%20in%20the%20job%20description%3C%2Fh3%3E%3Cp%3EAhead%20of%20the%20interview%2C%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fhow-to-leverage-a-job-description-to-get-ahead-of-the-competition-2021-8%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Eread%20the%20job%20description%20carefully%3C%2Fa%3E%20to%20identify%20the%20hard%20skills%20that%20are%20most%20important%20to%20do%20the%20job%20and%20take%20some%20time%20to%20build%20skills%20in%20the%20required%20area.%20Watch%20videos%20or%20practice%20where%20you%20can.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EIn%20the%20interview%2C%20note%20that%20this%20is%20a%20newer%20area%20of%20knowledge%20for%20you%2C%20but%20highlight%20the%20work%20you've%20already%20done%20to%20learn%20the%20skills%20in%20this%20area.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EIf%20you%20have%20no%20experience%20with%20a%20certain%20skill%2C%20make%20sure%20to%20list%20the%20adjacent%20skills%20that%20you%20do%20have.%20Maybe%20you%20haven't%20used%20Power%20BI%2C%20but%20you're%20a%20pro%20at%20Tableau.%20Or%20you've%20never%20coded%20in%20Python%2C%20but%20you%20know%20Java%20and%20Ruby%20on%20Rails.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EHighlight%20what%20you%20bring%20to%20the%20table.%20Perhaps%20you%20don't%20speak%20fluent%20Spanish%2C%20but%20you're%20good%20at%20using%20a%20translation%20app%20alongside%20your%20intermediate%20Spanish%20skills%20to%20get%20by%20in%20most%20conversations.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EAlso%2C%20share%20examples%20of%20other%20times%20you've%20quickly%20gotten%20up%20to%20speed%20in%20a%20new%20area.%20This%20will%20show%20that%2C%20while%20you're%20learning%2C%20you're%20also%20someone%20with%20a%20lot%20of%20initiative%20and%20won't%20be%20held%20back%20by%20a%20lack%20of%20experience%20in%20one%20small%20area.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Ch2%3ELies%20can%20end%20up%20being%20more%20damaging%3C%2Fh2%3E%3Cp%3EIn%20a%20tough%20job%20market%2C%20it%20can%20be%20tempting%20to%20lie.%20But%20in%20the%20long%20run%2C%20these%20lies%20will%20often%20be%20uncovered%20at%20some%20point%20in%20the%20process%20and%20could%20be%20more%20damaging%20to%20you%20than%20just%20being%20honest%20in%20the%20first%20place.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%3Cem%3EBonnie%20Dilber%20is%20the%20business%20recruiting%20team%20lead%20at%20Zapier.%20Before%20moving%20into%20tech%2C%20she%20spent%20years%20in%20education%20and%20nonprofits%20as%20a%20teacher%2C%20program%20m