th-koreas-kim-ju-ae%2Famp_articleshow%2F108674552.cms%22%2C%22ampUrl%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Ftimesofindia.indiatimes.com%2Fworld%2Frest-of-world%2Fthe-great-successor-who-is-north-koreas-kim-ju-ae%2Famp_articleshow%2F108674552.cms%22%7D%2C%7B%22title%22%3A%22Time%20to%20Have%20a%20Proper%20Code%20of%20Conduct%20in%20India%20Inc%20Boards%22%2C%22content%22%3A%22%3Cimg%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fthewire.in%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2F2016%2F12%2Fboardroom.jpeg%5C%22%3E%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EIndian%20stock%20markets%20may%20be%20growing%20but%20are%20plagued%20by%20many%20distorting%20forces%20including%20price-rigging%2C%20insider%20trading%2C%20opaque%20financials%20and%20overall%20poor%20adherence%20to%20regulation.%20Clearly%2C%20these%20are%20indicators%20of%20poor%20governance%20and%20an%20absence%20of%20a%20proper%20code%20of%20conduct%20in%20boards.%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EA%20couple%20of%20years%20ago%20five%20out%20of%2024%20insider%20trading%20cases%20investigsated%20by%20SEBI%20were%20Adani%20Group%20companies%20and%20there%20was%20also%20the%20allegation%20that%20one%20of%20the%20SEBI%20directors%20investigating%20was%20a%20relative%20of%20Adani.%20%C2%A0Even%20the%20darling%20of%20stock%20markets%20Reliance%20was%20found%20to%20indulge%20in%20insider%20trading%20and%20was%20%3C%2Fspan%3E%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Findianexpress.com%2Farticle%2Fbusiness%2Frpl-insider-trading-case-sebi-fines-reliance-mukesh-ambani-7129384%2F%23%3A~%3Atext%3DThe%2520market%2520regulator%2520has%2520levied%2Con%2520RIL%2520and%2520Ambani%252C%2520respectively.%5C%22%3E%3Cspan%3Efined%20Rs%2025%20crore%20and%20Ambani%20was%20fined%20Rs%2015%20crore%20in%20recent%20years%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fa%3E%3Cspan%3E.%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EFrom%20Satyam%20and%20IL%26amp%3BFS%20to%20Kingfisher%20and%20Jet%20and%20Adani%2C%20there%20have%20been%20numerous%20cases.%20Crucial%20to%20eliminating%20this%20%3C%2Fspan%3E%3Cspan%3Eis%20the%20adherence%20to%20ethical%20behaviour%2C%20starting%20at%20the%20board%20level.%20The%3C%2Fspan%3E%20%3Cspan%3Eindependent%20directors%20need%20to%20play%20a%20truly%20independent%20role%20in%20holding%20management%20accountable.%C2%A0%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EThere%20are%20some%20common%20issues%20related%20to%20poor%20board%20code%20of%20conduct%20in%20Indian%20enterprises.%20First%20is%20the%20dominance%20of%20promoters%20in%20the%20boardrooms.%20In%20many%20Indian%20companies%2C%20promoters%20(founders%20or%20controlling%20shareholders)%20hold%20significant%20influence%20on%20the%20board.%20This%20makes%20it%20difficult%20for%20independent%20directors%20to%20raise%20concerns%20or%20challenge%20management%20decisions.%20Second%20is%20the%20lack%20of%20independent%20oversight.%20Sometimes%2C%20independent%20directors%20may%20not%20have%20the%20necessary%20expertise%20or%20resources%20to%20scrutinise%20complex%20financial%20statements%20or%20business%20decisions.%20Finally%2C%20there%20are%20conflicts%20of%20interest.%20Board%20members%20might%20have%20personal%20or%20financial%20ties%20to%20the%20company%20or%20its%20management%2C%20creating%20a%20conflict%20of%20interest%20that%20hinders%20objective%20decision-making.%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3ETypically%2C%20there%20are%20three%20major%20unethical%20practices%20India%20Inc%20should%20be%20cognizant%20of%2C%20and%20avoid%20in%20developing%20a%20code%20of%20conduct.%20One%2C%20insider%20trading%2C%20which%20%3C%2Fspan%3E%3Cspan%3Eoccurs%20when%20directors%20or%20someone%20else%20on%20their%20behalf%20trade%20stocks%20based%20on%20privy%20confidential%20information.%20This%20unethical%20practice%20is%20against%20the%20market%20integrity%20and%20torpedoes%20investor%20confidence.%20Insider%20traders%20gain%20an%20unfair%20advantage%20over%20other%20investors.%20Not%20only%20does%20this%20violate%20the%20principle%20of%20fairness%20but%20also%20the%20integrity%20of%20stock%20exchanges.%20Most%20regulators%20have%20banned%20this%20across%20the%20world%20and%20it%20is%20illegal.%20The%20low%20penalties%20in%20India%20are%20not%20a%20deterrent%20unless%20combined%20with%20jail%20term.%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EEthical%20and%20legal%20standards%20are%20a%20must%20for%20board%20members%20to%20avoid%20the%20incidents%20of%20insider%20trading.%20The%20maintenance%20of%20strict%20confidentiality%20and%20restriction%20on%20own%20enterprise%20stock%20trading%20might%20be%20necessary.%20The%20code%20of%20conduct%20must%20outline%20clear%20policies%20and%20procedures%20that%20prohibit%20insider%20trading%2C%20along%20with%20educating%20board%20members%20about%20their%20obligations.%C2%A0%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3ETwo%2C%20bribery%20and%20corruption%2C%20which%20involve%20giving%2C%20offering%2C%20receiving%20or%20soliciting%20money%2C%20favours%20or%20benefits%20to%20influence%20business%20decisions%20or%20get%20undue%20advantages%20over%20rivals.%20Though%20the%20Modi%20government%20preached%20clean%20governance%2C%20the%20electoral%20bonds%20saga%20unfolding%20currently%20shows%20a%20totally%20different%20picture%20in%20this%20respect.%20How%20the%20State%20Bank%20of%20India%20(SBI)%20board%20will%20react%20to%20the%20chairman%E2%80%99s%20behaviour%20against%20Supreme%20Court%20order%20will%20be%20interesting%20to%20watch.%20Unless%20Indian%20mindset%20is%20totally%20against%20this%2C%20it%20is%20not%20easy%20to%20find%20a%20solution%20other%20than%20enforcing%20stringent%20laws%20like%20in%20the%20Nordic%20countries%20or%20the%20USA.%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EWhen%20board%20members%20engage%20in%20bribery%20and%20corruption%2C%20they%20encourage%20unfair%20competition%2C%20distort%20business%20decisions%2C%20and%20work%20against%20the%20company%E2%80%99s%20written%20values.%20The%20code%20of%20conduct%20must%20explicitly%20promote%3C%2Fspan%3E%20%3Cspan%3Etransparency%20and%20ethical%20behaviour.%20A%20robust%20internal%20control%20mechanism%20should%20be%20put%20in%20place%2C%20and%20a%20thorough%20due%20diligence%20on%20business%20partners%20must%20be%20undertaken.%20Offer%20anti-corruption%20training%20if%20needed.%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cins%3EAlso%20read%3A%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fthewire.in%2Fpolitics%2Fbjp-received-almost-90-of-all-corporate-donations-to-political-parties-in-2022-23%5C%22%3EBJP%20Received%20Almost%2090%25%20of%20All%20Corporate%20Donations%20to%20Political%20Parties%20in%202022-23%3C%2Fa%3E%3C%2Fins%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EThree%2C%20not%20acting%20in%20the%20best%20interests%20of%20shareholders.%20This%20is%20a%20neglect%20of%20the%20board%E2%80%99s%20fiduciary%20responsibilities.%20This%20unethical%20behaviour%20can%20lead%20to%20decisions%20that%20will%20benefit%20a%20select%20few%2C%20or%20neglect%20the%20larger%20enterprise%20interests.%20Such%20neglect%20of%20fiduciary%20duties%20can%20lead%20to%20legal%20action%20against%20the%20board%20including%20shareholder%20lawsuits%2C%20regulatory%20investigations%20or%20ED%20action%20(not%20necessarily%20for%20Electoral%20Bonds).%20In%20all%20these%20cases%2C%20financial%20penalties%20will%20be%20levied%2C%20not%20to%20mention%20reputation%20damage%20and%20even%20removal%20as%20board%20members%20%E2%80%94%20all%20these%20will%20result%20in%20possible%20loss%20of%20market%20value%20as%20in%20Adani%20and%20Hindenberg%20report.%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EA%20proper%20board%20code%20of%20conduct%20serves%20as%20a%20guiding%20framework%20to%20uphold%20integrity%2C%20ethics%2C%20and%20accountability%20in%20their%20roles%20as%20stewards%20of%20corporate%20governance.%20Here%20are%20some%20components%20of%20board%20code%20of%20conduct%20India%20Inc%20can%20adopt%3A%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cb%3EEthical%20standards%20and%20integrity%3A%3C%2Fb%3E%3Cspan%3E%20Directors%20are%20expected%20to%20act%20with%20honesty%2C%20transparency%2C%20and%20fairness%20in%20all%20their%20dealings%2C%20both%20within%20the%20organisation%20and%20with%20external%20stakeholders.%20Avoid%20conflicts%20of%20interest%2C%20respect%20confidentiality%2C%20and%20adhere%20to%20legal%20and%20regulatory%20requirements.%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cb%3EFiduciary%20duties%20and%20responsibilities%3A%3C%2Fb%3E%3Cspan%3E%20Outline%20these%20duties%2C%20including%20the%20duty%20of%20care%2C%20duty%20of%20loyalty%2C%20and%20duty%20of%20obedience.%20Directors%20are%20expected%20to%20exercise%20due%20diligence%2C%20prudence%2C%20and%20independent%20judgement%20in%20fulfilling%20their%20responsibilities%20and%20making%20decisions%20that%20benefit%20the%20company%20as%20a%20whole.%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cb%3EBoardroom%20behaviour%20and%20collaboration%3A%3C%2Fb%3E%3Cspan%3E%20Proper%20boardroom%20behaviour%20is%20essential%20for%20a%20culture%20of%20respect%2C%20professionalism%2C%20and%20collaboration%20among%20directors.%20Specify%20expectations%20for%20meetings%2C%20including%20punctuality%2C%20preparedness%2C%20active%20participation%2C%20and%20constructive%20dialogue.%20Directors%20should%20demonstrate%20mutual%20respect%2C%20listen%20to%20diverse%20viewpoints%2C%20and%20work%20together%20to%20achieve%20common%20goals.%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cb%3EConfidentiality%20and%20information%20security%3A%3C%2Fb%3E%3Cspan%3E%20Board%C2%A0%20has%20access%20to%20sensitive%20and%20confidential%20information%20about%20the%20company%2C%20its%20operations%2C%20and%20its%20strategic%20plans.%20Emphasise%20the%20importance%20of%20maintaining%20confidentiality%20and%20safeguarding%20proprietary%20information.%20Directors%20should%20exercise%20discretion%20and%20caution%20when%20handling%20confidential%20matters%20and%20avoid%20disclosing%20privileged%20information%20without%20proper%20authorisation.%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cb%3ECompliance%20and%20regulatory%20requirements%3A%20%3C%2Fb%3E%3Cspan%3ECompliance%20with%20laws%2C%20regulations%2C%20and%20corporate%20governance%20standards%20is%20critical.%20Directors%20must%20stay%20informed%20about%20applicable%20laws%20and%20regulations%2C%20adhere%20to%20corporate%20policies%20and%20procedures%2C%20and%20disclose%20any%20potential%20conflicts%20of%20interest.%C2%A0%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EIn%20the%20end%2C%20a%20company%20will%20be%20mostly%20as%20ethical%20as%20its%20founders%20are.%20In%20the%20midst%20of%20the%20current%20EB%20episode%2C%20Biocon%20chief%20Kiran%20Mazumdar%20Shaw%20was%20one%20of%20the%20first%20to%20come%20out%20and%20clarify%20the%20donations%20publicly.%20Salute%20to%20such%20chairpersons!%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cem%3EM.%20Muneer%20is%20a%20Fortune-500%20advisor%2C%20startup%20investor%20and%20co-founder%20of%20the%20non-profit%20Medici%20Institute%20for%20Innovation.%20He%20tweets%20%40MuneerMuh.%3C%2Fem%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cbr%3E%3Cbr%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%22%2C%22published%22%3A1711011644000%2C%22visual%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fthewire.in%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2F2016%2F12%2Fboardroom.jpeg%22%2C%22originID%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fthewire.in%2Fbusiness%2Ftime-to-have-a-proper-code-of-conduct-in-india-inc-boards%22%2C%22summary%22%3A%22When%20board%20members%20engage%20in%20bribery%20and%20corruption%2C%20they%20encourage%20unfair%20competition%2C%20distort%20business%20decisions%2C%20and%20work%20against%20the%20company%E2%80%99s%20written%20values.%20The%20code%20of%20conduct%20must%20explicitly%20promote%20transparency%20and%20ethical%20behaviour.%22%2C%22author%22%3A%22%22%2C%22engagement%22%3A0%2C%22canonicalUrl%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fthewire.in%2Fbusiness%2Ftime-to-have-a-proper-code-of-conduct-in-india-inc-boards%22%2C%22cdnAmpUrl%22%3A%22%22%2C%22ampUrl%22%3A%22%22%7D%2C%7B%22title%22%3A%22France%20Televisions%20Orders%20%E2%80%98Lucky%20Luke%E2%80%99%20With%20%E2%80%98Lost%20Bullet%E2%80%99%20Star%20Alban%20Lenoir%20and%20Period%20Female-Led%20Racing%20Show%20%E2%80%98Rallye%2082%E2%80%99%20(EXCLUSIVE)%2