E%3Cem%3ELive%20Law%3C%2Fem%3E%3C%2Fa%3E%2C%20the%20Supreme%20Court%20bench%20said%2C%20%E2%80%9CQuite%20apart%20from%20the%20statement%20made%20by%20the%20Union%20government%2C%20the%20challenges%20to%20the%20rule%20involves%20serious%20constitutional%20questions.%20The%20impact%20of%20Rule%203(1)(b)(v)%20on%20the%20fundamental%20right%20to%20freedom%20of%20speech%20and%20expression%20would%20fall%20for%20analysis%20by%20the%20High%20Court.%E2%80%9D%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20bench%20comprising%20of%20Chief%20Justice%20of%20India%20D.Y.%20Chandrachud%2C%20Justices%20J.B.%20Pardiwala%20and%20Manoj%20Misra%20%3Cb%3E%3C%2Fb%3E%20added%3A%20%E2%80%9CHowever%2C%20we%20are%20clearly%20of%20the%20view%20that%20the%20notification%20dated%20March%2020%2C%202024%2C%20issued%20by%20the%20Union%20Govt%20after%20the%20rejection%20of%20the%20application%20for%20interim%20relief%2C%20would%20need%20to%20be%20stayed.%E2%80%9D%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20stay%20will%20be%20valid%20till%20the%20disposal%20of%20the%20proceedings%20challenging%20validity%20of%20the%20fact-checking%20unit%20before%20the%20Bombay%20high%20court.%20Earlier%20this%20month%2C%20the%20high%20court%20had%20said%20that%20there%20will%20be%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fthewire.in%2Flaw%2Fno-interim-stay-notification-fact-checking-unit-bombay-hc%5C%22%3Eno%20interim%20stay%3C%2Fa%3E%20on%20the%20Union%20government%20notifying%20the%20fact-checking%20unit%2C%20a%20month%C2%A0after%20a%20two-judge%20bench%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fthewire.in%2Frights%2Fbombay-hc-split-verdict-petition-it-amendment-rules%5C%22%3Edelivered%20a%20split%20verdict%3C%2Fa%3E%20on%20the%20validity%20of%20the%20specific%20rule%20dealing%20with%20said%20unit.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EOn%20March%2020%2C%20the%20Union%20electronics%20and%20IT%20ministry%20had%20notified%20the%20FCU%20as%20a%20statutory%20body%20with%20powers%20to%20flag%20what%20it%20believes%20is%20false%20information%20related%20to%20the%20Central%20government%20and%20its%20agencies%20on%20social%20media%20sites.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20petitions%20were%20filed%20by%20Kunal%20Kamra%2C%20Editors%20Guild%20of%20India%20and%20Association%20of%20Indian%20Magazines%20challenging%20the%20refusal%20of%20the%20Bombay%20high%20court%20to%20stay%20the%20implementation%20of%20the%20IT%20Rules%202023.%20As%20per%20a%3Cem%3E%20Live%20Law%3C%2Fem%3E%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.livelaw.in%2Ftop-stories%2Fsupreme-court-kunal-kamra-editors-guild-notifying-fact-check-unit-it-rules-2023-252998%5C%22%3Ereport%3C%2Fa%3E%2C%20the%20CJI-led%20bench%20was%20of%20the%20view%20that%20there%20existed%20prima%20facie%20grounds%20for%20staying%20the%20notification%20dated%20March%2020%2C%20which%20makes%20the%20impugned%20Rules%20operational.%3Cb%3E%3C%2Fb%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EAs%20%3Cem%3EThe%20Wire%3C%2Fem%3E%20has%20reported%20in%20the%20past%2C%20there%20are%20serious%20concerns%20regarding%20the%20PIB%E2%80%99s%20ability%20to%20function%20as%20an%20independent%20body%20that%20will%20conduct%20fair%20fact-checks.%20Researchers%20at%20the%20Internet%20Freedom%20Foundation%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fthewire.in%2Fgovernment%2Fout-of-nearly-1-2-lakh-queries-in-3-years-pibs-fact-check-unit-acted-on-1223%5C%22%3Efound%3C%2Fa%3E%20that%20the%20PIB%20reveals%20having%20received%20nearly%201.2%20lakh%20requests%20for%20fact%20checking%20information%20on%20the%20internet%20in%20the%20last%20three%20years%2C%20i.e.%20since%20April%202020%2C%20whereas%20it%20has%20only%20acted%20upon%201%2C223%20of%20them%20%E2%80%93%20a%20modest%201%25%20action%20rate.%3C%2Fp%3E%22%2C%22published%22%3A1711010131000%2C%22visual%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fcdn.thewire.in%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2F2023%2F04%2F21234509%2FUntitled-design-86-1.png%22%2C%22originID%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fthewire.in%2Flaw%2Fsupreme-court-stays-union-governments-notification-on-pib-fact-check-unit%22%2C%22summary%22%3A%22On%20March%2020%2C%20the%20Union%20electronics%20and%20IT%20minis