0are%20being%20denied%20access%20to%20water%20from%20the%20community-bore-well%20of%20the%20village.%20In%20this%20state%2C%20sadly%2C%20even%20dead%20Christians%20are%20not%20spared%20as%20many%20were%20denied%20burial%20as%20per%20Christian%20rituals.%20Local%20villagers%20have%20been%20threatening%20to%20cremate%20the%20bodies%20as%20a%20final%20act%20of%20Gharwapasi.%20As%20in%20the%20Christmas%20period%20of%202022%2C%20Christians%20are%20again%20being%20chased%20out%20of%20their%20own%20homes.%20Locals%20are%20physically%20assaulting%2C%20threatening%20their%20lives%20and%20vandalizing%20their%20homes%2C%E2%80%9D%20UCF%20has%20said.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EIn%20Uttar%20Pradesh%2C%20which%20saw%20the%20second%20highest%20number%20of%20incidents%20after%20Chhattisgarh%2C%20there%20is%20%E2%80%9Cclear%20evidence%20of%20state-%20sponsored%20harassment%20of%20Christians%E2%80%9D%20as%20%E2%80%9Cthe%20police%20files%20false%20allegations%20of%20conversion%20against%20the%20pastors%20even%20for%20praying%20in%20birthday%20parties%20and%20other%20social%20gatherings%E2%80%9D%2C%20the%20release%20continues.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%E2%80%9CIn%20all%2C%20there%20are%2019%20states%20in%20India%20wherein%20Christians%20are%20facing%20threat%20to%20their%20lives%20for%20practicing%20their%20faith.%20There%20are%20122%20Christians%20who%20have%20either%20been%20detained%20or%20arrested%20on%20the%20false%20allegation%20of%20conversions%20in%20just%2075%20days%20of%202024.%20As%20UCF%2C%20we%20request%20our%20leadership%20to%20put%20an%20end%20to%20this%20violence%20by%20taking%20strict%20action%20against%20perpetrators%20of%20all%20such%20crimes%2C%20and%20we%20hope%20and%20pray%20for%20a%20peaceful%20and%20fair%20election%2C%E2%80%9D%20the%20group%20has%20stated.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fthewire.in%2Fcommunalism%2Fdata-rise-in-attacks-on-christians-in-india-up-four-times-in-11-years-2012-2022%5C%22%3E%3Cem%3EThe%20Wire%3C%2Fem%3E%20has%20reported%3C%2Fa%3E%20how%20attacks%20on%20Christians%20have%20seen%20a%20steep%20rise%20in%20the%20last%2014%20years%2C%20particularly%20since%202017.%20%E2%80%9CMost%20of%20the%20time%2C%20FIRs%20are%20filed%20against%20the%20victims%20of%20violence%2C%20while%20the%20perpetrators%20are%20allowed%20to%20go%20scot-free%2C%E2%80%9D%20A.C.%20Michael%2C%20national%20convenor%20of%20the%20UCF%2C%20told%C2%A0%3Cem%3EThe%20Wire%20%3C%2Fem%3Ethen.%20%E2%80%9COtherwise%20the%20police%20usually%20tries%20to%20pacify%20the%20victims%2C%20saying%20if%20you%20file%20a%20case%20then%20they%20%5Bthe%20attackers%5D%20may%20become%20more%20aggressive%2C%20and%20then%20your%20life%20will%20be%20more%20dangerous.%E2%80%9D%3C%2Fp%3E%22%2C%22published%22%3A1711003536000%2C%22visual%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fcdn.thewire.in%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2F2023%2F02%2F14184445%2Fpexels-m-15226359.jpg%22%2C%22originID%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fthewire.in%2Fcommunalism%2Fmore-than-150-attacks-on-indian-christians-in-2024-so-far-ucf%22%2C%22summary%22%3A%22%26quot%3BJanuary%20witnessed%2070%20incidents%20of%20violence%20against%20Christians%20followed%20by%2062%20incidents%20in%2029%20days%20of%20February%20and%2029%20incidents%20in%2015%20days%20of%20March%2C%202024.%26quot%3B%22%2C%22author%22%3A%22%22%2C%22engagement%22%3A4%2C%22canonicalUrl%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fthewire.in%2Fcommunalism%2Fmore-than-150-attacks-on-indian-christians-in-2024-so-far-ucf%22%2C%22cdnAmpUrl%22%3A%22%22%2C%22ampUrl%22%3A%22%22%7D%2C%7B%22title%22%3A%22Neuralink%20patient%20seen%20playing%20chess%20using%20brain%20implant%22%2C%22content%22%3A%22%22%2C%22published%22%3A1711003416000%2C%22visual%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fichef.bbci.co.uk%2Fnews%2F1024%2Fbranded_news%2F3F45%2Fproduction%2F_132979161_p0hkylw4.jpg%22%2C%22originID%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.bbc.co.uk%2Fnews%2Ftechnology-68623380%232%22%2C%22summary%22%3A%22In%20a%20livestream%20on%20X%2C%20the%20patient%20explained%20that%20he%20was%20using%20a%20device%20in%20his%20brain%20to%20move%20the%20cursor.%22%2C%22author%22%3A%22%22%2C%22engagement%22%3A67%2C%22canonicalUrl%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.bbc.co.uk%2Fnews%2Fav%2Ftechnology-68623380%22%2C%22cdnAmpUrl%22%3A%22%22%2C%22ampUrl%22%3A%22%22%7D%2C%7B%22title%22%3A%22Trial%20Delay%2C%20Prolonged%20Jail%20Cause%20for%20Bail%20Despite%20Section%2045%20of%20PMLA%3A%20SC%22%2C%22content%22%3A%22%3Cimg%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fcdn.thewire.in%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2F2024%2F01%2F25132016%2FSupreme-court4.jpeg%5C%22%3E%3Cp%3E%3Cstrong%3ENew%20Delhi%3A%3C%2Fstrong%3E%20The%20Supreme%20Court%20has%20orally%20observed%20that%20delay%20in%20trial%20and%20prolonged%20imprisonment%20makes%20an%20accused%20eligible%20for%20bail%20despite%20the%20Section%2045%20of%20the%20Prevention%20of%20Money%20Laundering%20Act.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.livelaw.in%2Ftop-stories%2Fs45-pmla-doesnt-bar-power-of-court-to-grant-bail-if-theres-delay-in-trial-justice-sanjiv-khanna-252861%23%3A~%3Atext%3DSupreme%2520Court%2520judge%2520Justice%2520Sanjiv%2Cincarceration%2520and%2520delay%2520in%2520trial.%5C%22%3E%3Cem%3ELiveLaw%3C%2Fem%3E%3C%2Fa%3E%20has%20reported%20that%20apex%20court%20judge%20Justice%20Sanjiv%20Khanna%20on%20March%2020%20observed%20that%20the%20section%20does%20not%20bar%20an%20accused%20from%20bail%20on%20the%20ground%20of%20prolonged%20incarceration%20%E2%80%93%20which%20is%20something%20which%20flows%20from%20Article%2021%20of%20the%20constitution.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20Section%2045%20has%20it%20that%20an%20accused%20can%20only%20be%20granted%20bail%20if%20the%20court%20is%20prima%20facie%20satisfied%20that%20he%20has%20not%20committed%20an%20offence%20and%20is%20likely%20to%20not%20commit%20it%20while%20on%20bail.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EJustice%20Khanna%20cited%20the%20judgment%20in%20former%20Delhi%20deputy%20chief%20minister%20Manish%20Sisodia%E2%80%99s%20case%2C%20where%20Sisodia%20was%20granted%20liberty%20to%20apply%20for%20bail%20if%20there%20was%20delay%20in%20trial.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cem%3ELiveLaw%3C%2Fem%3E%20has%20further%20reported%20that%20the%20bench%2C%20also%20comprising%20Justice%20Dipankar%20Datta%2C%C2%A0was%20hearing%20the%20bail%20application%20of%20one%20Prem%20Prakash%2C%20who%20is%20alleged%20to%20be%20the%20aide%20of%20Jharkhand%20Chief%20Minister%20Hemant%20Soren%20in%20a%20money%20laundering%20case.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EPrakash%20has%20spent%2018%20months%20in%20jail%2C%20Justice%20Khanna%20told%20Additional%20Solicitor%20General%20S.V.%20Raju.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%E2%80%9CThat%20constitutional%20right%20is%20not%20taken%20away%20by%20Section%2045.%20It%20is%20very%20clear%2C%E2%80%9D%20Justice%20Khanna%20said.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EWhen%20ASG%20Raju%20said%20that%20Section%20436A%20of%20the%20Criminal%20Procedure%20Code%20has%20it%20that%20an%20undertrial%20has%20to%20spend%20at%20least%2050%25%20of%20the%20maximum%20sentence%20to%20seek%20bail%20on%20the%20ground%20of%20delay%2C%C2%A0Justice%20Khanna%20said%20that%20this%20is%20%E2%80%9Conly%20an%20enabling%20provision%E2%80%9D%20and%20does%20not%20disable%20the%20court%20from%20granting%20bail.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EHowever%2C%20the%20bench%20did%20not%20grant%20bail%20to%20Prakash%20and%20adjourned%20the%20hearing%20by%20a%20month%20to%20ascertain%20the%20progress%20of%20trial%2C%20asking%20the%20court%20to%20expedite%20it.%3C%2Fp%3E%22%2C%22published%22%3A1711003077000%2C%22visual%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fcdn.thewire.in%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2F2024%2F01%2F25132016%2FSupreme-court4.jpeg%22%2C%22originID%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fthewire.in%2Flaw%2Ftrial-delay-prolonged-jail-cause-for-bail-despite-section-45-of-pmla-sc%22%2C%22summary%22%3A%22Apex%20court%20judge%20Justice%20Sanjiv%20Khanna%20on%20March%2020%20observed%20that%20the%20section%20does%20not%20bar%20an%20accused%20from%20bail%20on%20the%20ground%20of%20prolonged%20incarceration.%22%2C%22author%22%3A%22%22%2C%22engagement%22%3A6%2C%22canonicalUrl%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fthewire.in%2Flaw%2Ftrial-delay-pr